  ('abcab60f-7764-8e37-4949-fb60da595bf0', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Limone di Rocca Imperiale IGP', '["Limone di Rocca Imperiale IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Calabrian lemon from Rocca Imperiale area, characteristic small-medium fruit with thin peel and very juicy flesh, balanced acidity, fragrant.', 'Fresh juice, Calabrian seafood, pastry, citrus salads.', '["crate-10kg", "crate-15kg", "retail-net-bag-2kg"]'::jsonb, '[10, 11, 12, 1, 2, 3, 4]'::jsonb, '["Limone Rocca Imperiale"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('ad12d35f-407e-4f84-7731-4047ee50e4d0', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Limone di Siracusa IGP', '["Limone di Siracusa IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Sicilian lemon from Siracusa province, Femminello Siracusano variety. Bright yellow, three flowering cycles per year (Primofiore winter, Bianchetto spring, Verdello summer), juicy aromatic flesh.', 'Fresh juice, Sicilian seafood (raw fish, swordfish), granita, pastry, ricotta-lemon desserts, Cassata ingredient.', '["crate-10kg", "crate-15kg", "retail-net-bag-2kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Femminello Siracusano", "Siracusa lemon"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('d98b379c-62ed-be57-26c5-c91fd698b590', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Limone di Sorrento IGP', '["Limone di Sorrento IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Campanian lemon from Sorrento peninsula, "Femminello Ovale di Sorrento" variety. Oval-elliptical shape, thick aromatic peel, juicy fragrant flesh, distinct from Amalfi-Sfusato.', 'Limoncello (the original), Sorrento lemon-cream pasta (Pasta al limone di Sorrento), fresh juice, granita, pastry.', '["crate-10kg", "crate-15kg", "retail-net-bag-2kg"]'::jsonb, '[3, 4, 5, 6, 7]'::jsonb, '["Femminello Ovale di Sorrento", "Sorrento lemon"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('2f19f0dd-1b3d-2a57-52db-826c5c844c47', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Limone Femminello del Gargano IGP', '["Limone Femminello del Gargano IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Apulian lemon from Gargano peninsula. Bright yellow, juicy aromatic flesh, traditional cultivar.', 'Apulian seafood, fresh juice, Gargano-region pastry, limoncello.', '["crate-10kg", "retail-net-bag-2kg"]'::jsonb, '[10, 11, 12, 1, 2, 3, 4]'::jsonb, '["Femminello del Gargano"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('c856da1a-464a-df6e-937c-85ce8dcb0c34', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Limone Interdonato Messina IGP', '["Limone Interdonato Messina IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Sicilian lemon-citron hybrid from Messina coast, Interdonato variety (cross between citron and lemon). Distinctive elongated shape with smooth thin peel, less acidic than standard lemon, very juicy.', 'Fresh juice with milder profile, citrus salads, pastry, ricotta desserts.', '["crate-10kg", "retail-net-bag-2kg"]'::jsonb, '[10, 11, 12, 1]'::jsonb, '["Interdonato di Messina"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('bc57a40c-78df-0eda-d526-f623bd83966e', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Mandarino Tardivo di Ciaculli DOP', '["Mandarino Tardivo di Ciaculli DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Sicilian late-harvest mandarin from Ciaculli area near Palermo, Tardivo variety. Small bright orange fruit, very sweet juicy flesh, harvested late winter when most mandarins are out of season.', 'Premium fresh fruit, juice, dessert garnish.', '["crate-5kg", "crate-10kg", "retail-tray-500g"]'::jsonb, '[1, 2, 3]'::jsonb, '["Ciaculli mandarin", "Tardivo di Ciaculli"]'::jsonb, TRUE, 'L2'),
  ('6de7c79f-0de0-8c6c-07a2-b9166b01df62', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Mandorla di Toritto IGP', '["Mandorla di Toritto IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Apulian almond from Toritto (Bari province), three traditional varieties (Filippo Cea, Antonio De Vito, Genco). Sweet flavor with intense aromatic profile, oily texture, low bitter notes — among Italy''s premier almonds.', 'Pastry use (especially Apulian and Sicilian dolci), almond paste, marzipan, biscotti, in salads, candied (confetti), drink production (orgeat).', '["vacuum-pack-shelled-250g", "vacuum-pack-shelled-500g", "vacuum-pack-shelled-1kg", "bulk-shelled-5kg", "in-shell-bulk-10kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Toritto almond", "Filippo Cea (variety)"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('964de61b-1a98-5a7d-f41c-fd2852e2db8d', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Marrone della Valle di Susa IGP', '["Marrone della Valle di Susa IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Piedmontese chestnut from Susa valley, large mahogany shell, sweet creamy flesh.', 'Caldarroste, candied (marrons glacés), in autumn pasta dishes.', '["crate-10kg", "vacuum-pack-cooked-500g"]'::jsonb, '[10, 11, 12]'::jsonb, '["Marrone Susa"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('e06e6dab-9b28-699e-a5d5-37a657eeb54e', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Marrone del Mugello IGP', '["Marrone del Mugello IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Tuscan chestnut from Mugello area (Florence province), large pyramidal shape, sweet floury flesh, characteristic delicate aroma.', 'Caldarroste, candied, in Tuscan autumn cuisine, dried for Marrone flour and traditional Castagnaccio.', '["crate-10kg", "crate-15kg", "vacuum-pack-cooked-500g", "dried-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[10, 11, 12]'::jsonb, '["Marrone Mugello", "Mugello chestnut"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('9275c358-4e2d-e6bf-88ff-2e007f023209', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Marrone di Caprese Michelangelo DOP', '["Marrone di Caprese Michelangelo DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Tuscan chestnut from Caprese Michelangelo (Arezzo province, Michelangelo''s birthplace). Medium-large size, sweet flesh.', 'Caldarroste, in Tuscan dishes, candied.', '["crate-10kg", "crate-15kg"]'::jsonb, '[10, 11, 12]'::jsonb, '["Marrone di Caprese"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('0f2c7b4d-7910-5f54-9a7e-11dee23cc4e3', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Marrone di Castel del Rio IGP', '["Marrone di Castel del Rio IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Emilian chestnut from Imola hills (Bologna province), large shape, sweet flesh.', 'Caldarroste, candied, in Emilian autumn cuisine.', '["crate-10kg", "crate-15kg", "vacuum-pack-cooked-500g"]'::jsonb, '[10, 11, 12]'::jsonb, '["Castel del Rio chestnut"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('e4e6b2c9-7c7b-bdd6-91e9-66161febb656', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Marrone di Combai IGP', '["Marrone di Combai IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Veneto chestnut from Treviso prealps (Combai area), medium-large shape, sweet flesh, traditional autumn product.', 'Caldarroste (especially at Combai''s autumn chestnut festival), in Veneto autumn dishes.', '["crate-10kg", "crate-15kg"]'::jsonb, '[10, 11, 12]'::jsonb, '["Combai chestnut"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('9d147d84-ae21-d8bd-8234-373600940de2', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Marrone di Roccadaspide IGP', '["Marrone di Roccadaspide IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Campanian chestnut from Cilento hills (Roccadaspide), medium-large size, sweet creamy flesh.', 'Caldarroste, in Cilentan autumn cuisine, candied.', '["crate-10kg", "crate-15kg"]'::jsonb, '[10, 11, 12]'::jsonb, '["Roccadaspide chestnut"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('b2d66819-5957-1d8e-0770-b467fbb4f8f4', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Marrone di San Zeno DOP', '["Marrone di San Zeno DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Veneto chestnut from Lake Garda foothills (San Zeno di Montagna), large mahogany shell, sweet aromatic flesh.', 'Caldarroste, candied, in Veneto autumn dishes.', '["crate-10kg", "crate-15kg"]'::jsonb, '[10, 11, 12]'::jsonb, '["San Zeno chestnut"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('af1b63a0-93e5-39ed-3124-4c0dfdf5d297', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Marroni del Monfenera IGP', '["Marroni del Monfenera IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Veneto chestnut from Monfenera hills (Treviso province), traditional medium-large chestnut with sweet flesh.', 'Caldarroste, candied, in Veneto autumn cuisine.', '["crate-10kg", "crate-15kg"]'::jsonb, '[10, 11, 12]'::jsonb, '["Monfenera chestnut"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('e33c43cd-0aec-2cee-78d4-380132e769e6', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Mela Alto Adige IGP', '["Mela Alto Adige IGP", "Südtiroler Apfel IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI", "PGI"]'::jsonb, 'South-Tyrolean apple, multiple varieties (Golden Delicious, Red Delicious, Gala, Fuji, Granny Smith, Pink Lady, Stark Delicious, Renette etc.). Italy''s largest apple production zone — characteristic uniform high quality, crisp texture, bright clean flavor profile by variety.', 'Fresh fruit, dessert apple in tarts and strudel (Tyrolean classic), salads, with cheese and Speck on antipasto, juice production.', '["crate-15kg", "crate-18kg", "retail-tray-2kg", "retail-net-bag-3kg", "controlled-atmosphere-bin-300kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Südtiroler Apfel", "Alto Adige apple", "Mela Val Venosta (sub-zone)", "South-Tyrolean apple"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('d24afb46-261a-8eb2-1a63-63494e0900c2', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Mela di Valtellina IGP', '["Mela di Valtellina IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Lombard apple from Valtellina valley, multiple varieties similar to Alto Adige. Crisp texture, balanced sweet-acid, bright flavor.', 'Fresh fruit, in Valtellinese desserts, paired with Bitto and Casera cheeses, juice production.', '["crate-15kg", "retail-tray-2kg", "retail-net-bag-3kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Valtellina apple", "Mela valtellinese"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('3987c96d-987e-8877-fb87-6966f3c25641', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Mela Rossa Cuneo IGP', '["Mela Rossa Cuneo IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Piedmontese red apple from Cuneo area, Red Delicious and Gala varieties. Bright red skin, crisp white flesh, sweet flavor.', 'Fresh fruit, salads, paired with Castelmagno and Gorgonzola, juice.', '["crate-15kg", "retail-tray-2kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Mela Cuneo", "Cuneo red apple"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('3b363c52-5c0b-5436-3699-d31446216119', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Mela Val di Non DOP', '["Mela Val di Non DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Trentino apple from Val di Non, Renetta Canada (premium traditional variety) plus Golden Delicious, Red Delicious. Renetta has rough golden skin, distinctive sweet-tart flavor with intense aromatic profile, firm slow-aging flesh — Italy''s most renowned regional apple.', 'Fresh fruit, in Tyrolean strudel and torta di mele (especially Renetta), salads, with Trentino cheeses, juice and grappa.', '["crate-15kg", "crate-18kg", "retail-tray-2kg", "retail-net-bag-3kg", "gift-tray-Renetta-1.5kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Renetta del Trentino", "Val di Non apple", "Melinda (commercial brand)"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('07933e26-7162-ecfb-0a12-7bd6c7fe4477', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Melannurca Campana IGP', '["Melannurca Campana IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Campanian apple "Annurca" — small reddish bicolor fruit, distinctive low-tree variety, traditional sun-ripening on straw beds ("melai"). Crisp white flesh, intensely fragrant, sweet-acid balanced flavor with wine-like notes.', 'Fresh dessert apple (especially with cheese), in Neapolitan baked apple desserts, paired with Provolone del Monaco, juice for cosmetic/health products.', '["crate-10kg", "retail-tray-1kg", "retail-net-bag-2kg"]'::jsonb, '[10, 11, 12, 1, 2]'::jsonb, '["Annurca", "Mela Annurca"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('64a6cf2b-de40-2feb-c698-c61e3c41c316', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Mele del Trentino IGP', '["Mele del Trentino IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Trentino regional IGP for multiple apple varieties (Golden Delicious, Red Delicious, Gala, Fuji, Renetta etc.). Quality production zone, crisp clean flavors.', 'Fresh fruit, dessert use, salads, juice.', '["crate-15kg", "retail-tray-2kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Mele Trentino", "Trentino apples"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('43d8473e-42cf-3806-2f30-7b45086a11da', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Melone Mantovano IGP', '["Melone Mantovano IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Mantovano melon (Cucumis melo varieties — Charentais, Honeydew, Cantaloupe styles). Bright orange or pale green flesh, fragrant sweet flavor, balanced moisture.', 'Classic with Prosciutto di Parma DOP (Melone e prosciutto antipasto), summer fruit dessert, sorbet, gazpacho-style cold soup, salads.', '["crate-10kg", "single-fruit-1.5-2kg", "retail-tray-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[6, 7, 8, 9]'::jsonb, '["Melone di Mantova"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('83ddb2ec-4167-6fc8-a5c5-eaf2bdc0bf79', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Nocciola del Piemonte IGP', '["Nocciola del Piemonte IGP", "Nocciola Piemonte IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI", "PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Piedmontese hazelnut, Tonda Gentile delle Langhe variety — globally regarded as the world''s premier hazelnut. Round shape, golden-brown shell, intensely aromatic flesh with sweet roasted-nut flavor, low oil-rancidity.', 'Pastry foundation (Nocciolata, Gianduja, Torta di nocciole, Tartufo dolce), praline production, ingredient in panettone and traditional cookies, ground for crumbles, in pesto trapanese variations.', '["vacuum-pack-shelled-250g", "vacuum-pack-shelled-500g", "vacuum-pack-shelled-1kg", "in-shell-bulk-10kg", "ground-paste-1kg", "ground-paste-bulk-5kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Tonda Gentile delle Langhe", "Tonda Gentile Trilobata", "Nocciola IGP", "Piedmont hazelnut"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('aab8649d-2182-71ea-2e5d-a1bf9684c679', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Nocciola di Giffoni IGP', '["Nocciola di Giffoni IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Campanian hazelnut from Giffoni Valle Piana area, "Tonda di Giffoni" variety. Round shape, sweet aromatic flavor, slightly different profile from Piedmont — classic for southern Italian pastry.', 'Pastry use, especially Campanian and Sicilian dolci, praline, gelato.', '["vacuum-pack-shelled-250g", "vacuum-pack-shelled-500g", "in-shell-bulk-10kg", "ground-paste-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Tonda di Giffoni", "Giffoni hazelnut"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('450c1a3e-5077-e435-736e-74ff8bb3033a', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Nocciola Romana DOP', '["Nocciola Romana DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Lazio hazelnut from Viterbo-Rome area, Tonda Gentile Romana and Nocchione varieties. Round shape, sweet aromatic flesh.', 'Pastry, praline, gelato, paired with chocolate.', '["vacuum-pack-shelled-250g", "vacuum-pack-shelled-500g", "in-shell-bulk-10kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Tonda Gentile Romana", "Roman hazelnut"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('aa760c57-310c-faa6-0d24-033dac37756d', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Pera dell''Emilia Romagna IGP', '["Pera dell''Emilia Romagna IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Emilian-Romagnolo pear, multiple varieties (Abate Fétel, Conference, Williams, Decana, Kaiser etc.). Italy''s largest pear production zone — uniform high quality, juicy fragrant flesh.', 'Fresh fruit, with Gorgonzola DOP and walnuts on cheese boards, in pear-and-cheese tart, poached pears, sorbet, juice.', '["crate-10kg", "crate-15kg", "retail-tray-1kg", "retail-tray-2kg"]'::jsonb, '[8, 9, 10, 11, 12, 1]'::jsonb, '["Pera Emilia", "Abate", "Conference (varietal names)"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('cb536eab-06dd-8c6b-4e8c-8e4d0b93e666', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Pera mantovana IGP', '["Pera mantovana IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Mantuan pear, multiple varieties, juicy fragrant flesh.', 'Fresh fruit, with cheese (Grana Padano, Mantovano), in regional desserts.', '["crate-10kg", "retail-tray-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[8, 9, 10, 11, 12]'::jsonb, '["Pera di Mantova"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2')
INSERT INTO gi_entries (gi_id, country_code, country, category, primary_gi_name, all_gi_names, gi_type_primary, gi_types_all, tasting_notes, horeca_use, packaging_formats, seasonal_months, aliases, is_data_thin, source_layer) VALUES
  ('fa9e5987-8642-00d5-fec0-51f3eb5be1d2', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Pesca di Leonforte IGP', '["Pesca di Leonforte IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Sicilian peach from Leonforte (Enna province), distinctive bag-protected variety harvested in autumn (later than typical Italian peach). White or yellow flesh, very juicy, sweet flavor, harvested when most peaches are out of season.', 'Premium fresh fruit, in autumn desserts, granita, sorbet, paired with Sicilian sweet wines.', '["crate-5kg", "crate-10kg", "retail-tray-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[9, 10, 11]'::jsonb, '["Leonforte peach", "Pesca tardiva di Leonforte"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('63725b0c-8c3b-d749-8bf8-ef19093753c5', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Pesca di Verona IGP', '["Pesca di Verona IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Veneto peach from Verona area, multiple varieties. Yellow or white flesh, juicy fragrant.', 'Fresh fruit, classic Bellini cocktail (white peach), summer desserts.', '["crate-5kg", "retail-tray-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[6, 7, 8]'::jsonb, '["Pesca di Verona"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('f57bbc32-f7eb-020f-43d6-c500f8b77a58', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Pesca e Nettarina di Romagna IGP', '["Pesca e Nettarina di Romagna IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Romagnolo peach and nectarine, multiple varieties. Yellow or white flesh, juicy fragrant flavor — Italy''s main peach production zone.', 'Fresh fruit, summer desserts, sorbet, peach-based cocktails (Bellini), preserves.', '["crate-5kg", "crate-10kg", "retail-tray-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[6, 7, 8, 9]'::jsonb, '["Pesche di Romagna", "Nettarine di Romagna"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('e22e9c56-e908-f3a8-4e42-318804062174', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Pescabivona IGP', '["Pescabivona IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Sicilian peach from Bivona area (Agrigento province), four traditional varieties (Murtiddara, Agostina, Bianca, Settembrina). Distinctive white-fleshed peach with intensely fragrant flavor, late-summer to early-autumn harvest.', 'Fresh fruit (premium late-season), Sicilian summer desserts, granita.', '["crate-5kg", "retail-tray-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[7, 8, 9]'::jsonb, '["Bivona peach", "Settembrina"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('102c74b0-9da6-e930-886f-32c4c600e0e9', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Pistacchio di Raffadali DOP', '["Pistacchio di Raffadali DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Sicilian pistachio from Raffadali (Agrigento province), Bianca/Napoletana variety. Smaller and more subtle than Bronte; characteristic green color, sweet flavor.', 'Pastry, gelato, savory garnish on pasta and rice dishes, ingredient in Sicilian dolci.', '["vacuum-pack-shelled-100g", "vacuum-pack-shelled-250g", "vacuum-pack-shelled-500g", "in-shell-200g", "ground-paste-200g", "ground-paste-500g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Raffadali pistachio"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('f1dd45ff-34f6-0261-8ca3-d99536a779ed', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Pistacchio Verde di Bronte DOP', '["Pistacchio Verde di Bronte DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Sicilian pistachio from Bronte (Etna foothills, Catania province), Napoletana variety on volcanic terraces. Distinctive vivid emerald-green color, intensely aromatic, sweet flavor, oily rich texture — globally the most prized pistachio, biennial harvest "annata di carico".', 'Premium pastry use (cassata, cannoli, gelato pistacchio, semifreddo), pesto al pistacchio for pasta, ingredient in mortadella, garnish on lamb and seafood, grain in Sicilian biscotti.', '["vacuum-pack-shelled-100g", "vacuum-pack-shelled-250g", "vacuum-pack-shelled-500g", "in-shell-200g", "ground-paste-200g", "ground-paste-500g", "ground-paste-bulk-1kg", "granella-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Bronte pistachio", "Pistacchio di Bronte", "Verde di Bronte"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('b1064ad0-c5c4-02a6-51e4-97c58a232ba0', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Susina di Dro DOP', '["Susina di Dro DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Trentino plum from Sarca valley (Dro area), Prugna di Dro variety. Small dark-purple fruit with greenish-yellow flesh, traditional fresh-and-dried product, balanced sweet-tart flavor with intense plum aroma.', 'Fresh fruit (limited season), dried prunes, in regional desserts, with Trentino cheeses.', '["crate-5kg-fresh", "vacuum-pack-dried-200g", "vacuum-pack-dried-500g"]'::jsonb, '[8, 9]'::jsonb, '["Prugna di Dro", "Dro plum"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('28c88012-c055-1f4d-58a8-fdebfa621107', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Uva da tavola di Canicattì IGP', '["Uva da tavola di Canicattì IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Sicilian table grape from Canicattì area (Agrigento province), Italia variety. Large amber-yellow grapes, balanced sweet flavor, characteristic Muscat aromatic notes.', 'Fresh fruit dessert, on cheese boards, decorative service for autumn-winter menus.', '["crate-5kg", "crate-10kg", "retail-tray-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[9, 10, 11, 12]'::jsonb, '["Uva di Canicattì"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('be89a066-4d77-9fed-e61b-48573375f201', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Uva da tavola di Mazzarrone IGP', '["Uva da tavola di Mazzarrone IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Sicilian table grape from Mazzarrone area (Catania province), multiple varieties (Italia, Black Magic, Red Globe, Vittoria, Sublima etc.). Large grapes, sweet juicy flavor, multi-color range from green to amber to deep purple.', 'Fresh fruit, cheese boards, fruit plates, decorative.', '["crate-5kg", "crate-10kg", "retail-tray-500g", "retail-tray-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[7, 8, 9, 10, 11]'::jsonb, '["Uva di Mazzarrone"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('fa1f7012-1cc3-f441-27c9-0877dac42eb0', 'IT', 'Italy', 'fruits_nuts', 'Uva di Puglia IGP', '["Uva di Puglia IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Apulian table grape regional IGP (Bari-Taranto provinces), multiple varieties (Italia, Vittoria, Red Globe, Crimson, Regina etc.). Large grapes, juicy sweet flavor, broad varietal selection.', 'Fresh fruit, cheese boards, decorative service.', '["crate-5kg", "crate-10kg", "retail-tray-500g", "retail-tray-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[7, 8, 9, 10, 11]'::jsonb, '["Uva da tavola di Puglia", "Apulian table grape"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('bf864973-748c-a566-6265-7f751b05c605', 'IT', 'Italy', 'seafood_conservas', 'Acciughe sotto sale del Mar Ligure IGP', '["Acciughe sotto sale del Mar Ligure IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Ligurian salt-cured anchovies from Riviera waters, traditional layered packing in salt for 3+ months. Pinkish-red firm fillets when cured, intense umami-savory flavor with deep marine notes, balanced salinity, tender melting texture.', 'Foundation of Ligurian cuisine — bagna cauda, anchovy-stuffed olives, sliced raw on bruschetta with butter, melted into pasta sauces (puttanesca, anchovy-walnut), in vitello tonnato; classic with Riviera Ligure DOP olive oil.', '["glass-jar-100g", "glass-jar-200g", "glass-jar-500g", "ceramic-pot-bulk-1kg", "wooden-box-traditional-1kg", "vacuum-pack-150g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Acciughe del Mar Ligure", "Ligurian salted anchovies"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('7741ecb0-e329-2560-d6d7-30bd10b616e1', 'IT', 'Italy', 'seafood_conservas', 'Cozza di Scardovari DOP', '["Cozza di Scardovari DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Veneto Adriatic mussels from Po delta lagoon (Scardovari sacca), Mytilus galloprovincialis. Plump orange-cream meat, distinctive sweet-briny flavor with characteristic delta-water minerality, firm tender texture; among Italy''s most prized lagoon mussels.', 'Premium fresh service — sautéed alla marinara, in zuppa di cozze, on linguine, gratin alla parmigiana; raw service on tasting menus; classic with Soave or Lugana wines.', '["mesh-bag-fresh-1kg", "mesh-bag-fresh-2kg", "mesh-bag-bulk-5kg", "vacuum-pack-cooked-500g"]'::jsonb, '[4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10]'::jsonb, '["Cozza di Scardovari", "Scardovari mussel", "Po delta mussel"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('2a29d59c-19df-90b0-c8d6-6c237e5a8481', 'IT', 'Italy', 'seafood_conservas', 'Salmerino del Trentino IGP', '["Salmerino del Trentino IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Trentino Arctic char (Salvelinus alpinus) from alpine lakes and aquaculture. Pinkish-orange flesh, delicate sweet-mild flavor with clean alpine-water character, tender texture between trout and salmon.', 'Pan-seared with butter and sage, baked with mountain herbs, smoked for antipasto, carpaccio service, paired with Trentino cheeses (Puzzone di Moena, Trentingrana).', '["whole-fresh-300-500g", "whole-fresh-bulk-3kg", "fillet-fresh-200g", "smoked-vacuum-100g", "smoked-vacuum-200g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Trentino char", "Alpine char"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('7704e7b1-a4d0-2383-2b7d-39be6b4feb9e', 'IT', 'Italy', 'seafood_conservas', 'Tinca Gobba Dorata del Pianalto di Poirino DOP', '["Tinca Gobba Dorata del Pianalto di Poirino DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Piedmontese golden tench (Tinca tinca) from Poirino plateau pond aquaculture, traditional centuries-old practice. Distinctive golden-bronze skin, white firm flesh, delicate sweet flavor with characteristic earthy-pond notes.', 'Pan-fried with sage and butter (classic Piedmontese preparation), in carpione (vinegared cold-cured), grilled, in regional risotto.', '["whole-fresh-200-500g", "whole-fresh-bulk-3kg"]'::jsonb, '[3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10]'::jsonb, '["Tinca di Poirino", "Golden tench Piedmont"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('651b6a78-21e9-2257-4f95-4e7b6b725762', 'IT', 'Italy', 'seafood_conservas', 'Trote del Trentino IGP', '["Trote del Trentino IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Trentino trout (rainbow Salmo gairdneri / brown Salmo trutta / brook Salvelinus fontinalis) from alpine streams and aquaculture. Pinkish-white flesh, delicate fresh flavor with clean alpine-water character, tender texture.', 'Pan-seared, baked, smoked for antipasto, carpaccio, classic with Trentino butter and sage; paired with regional white wines.', '["whole-fresh-250-500g", "fillet-fresh-200g", "smoked-vacuum-100g", "smoked-vacuum-200g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Trentino trout"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('87680636-5d60-1406-0901-ccdb055448a8', 'IT', 'Italy', 'vinegars_condiments', 'Aceto Balsamico di Modena IGP', '["Aceto Balsamico di Modena IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Modenese balsamic vinegar IGP — blend of cooked grape must and wine vinegar, aged minimum 60 days (Invecchiato 3+ years). Dark mahogany color, balanced sweet-acid profile with caramel and woody notes; commercial volume product distinct from Tradizionale DOP.', 'Versatile dressing on insalata caprese and rocket salads, finishing on grilled meats and vegetables, glazes for fish and pork, drizzled on strawberries and Parmigiano cubes; the most exported Italian vinegar.', '["glass-bottle-250ml", "glass-bottle-500ml", "glass-bottle-750ml", "glass-bottle-1L", "glass-jug-3L", "PET-canister-5L", "pump-bottle-500ml"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Aceto Balsamico", "ABM", "Modena balsamic", "Balsamico di Modena"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('e1c1d9b0-604e-34a3-1fd8-2437a093d15c', 'IT', 'Italy', 'vinegars_condiments', 'Aceto Balsamico Tradizionale di Modena DOP', '["Aceto Balsamico Tradizionale di Modena DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Modenese traditional balsamic DOP — pure cooked grape must (Trebbiano, Lambrusco), aged minimum 12 years in successive smaller barrels of different woods. Dense syrupy mahogany-black liquid, intensely complex sweet-acid balance with woody-dried-fruit-caramel notes; "Affinato" 12+ years, "Extra Vecchio" 25+ years — among the world''s most prized vinegars.', 'Finishing only — drops on aged Parmigiano cubes, on strawberries, on vanilla gelato; tasting menu component (often served in spoon at end of meal); never used for cooking; pairs with Lambrusco and aged Parmigiano.', '["sealed-glass-bottle-100ml-DOP-Affinato", "sealed-glass-bottle-100ml-DOP-ExtraVecchio", "3-bottle-gift-set-100ml"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["ABTM", "Tradizionale", "Aceto Balsamico Tradizionale", "Modena traditional balsamic"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('eec3ef67-23a5-2c25-3a1a-18d5d97bf595', 'IT', 'Italy', 'vinegars_condiments', 'Aceto Balsamico Tradizionale di Reggio Emilia DOP', '["Aceto Balsamico Tradizionale di Reggio Emilia DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Reggio Emilia traditional balsamic DOP — same production principle as Modena Tradizionale (cooked must, long wood-barrel aging) with three quality tiers identified by label color: Aragosta/Lobster (12+ yrs), Argento/Silver (18+ yrs), Oro/Gold (25+ yrs). Dense complex syrup with subtle differences from Modena Tradizionale (often slightly less acidic).', 'Same as Modena Tradizionale — finishing drops on Parmigiano, strawberries, gelato, tasting menus; never for cooking.', '["sealed-glass-bottle-100ml-Aragosta", "sealed-glass-bottle-100ml-Argento", "sealed-glass-bottle-100ml-Oro", "gift-set-three-tiers"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["ABTRE", "Tradizionale di Reggio", "Reggio traditional balsamic"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('453eb72b-c6d7-541d-f34c-e6a2c6c6ec91', 'IT', 'Italy', 'vinegars_condiments', 'Colatura di Alici di Cetara DOP', '["Colatura di Alici di Cetara DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Campanian fish-sauce condiment from Cetara (Amalfi coast), pure liquid extracted from anchovies salted in chestnut barrels for 3-9+ months. Amber translucent color, intensely savory umami flavor with concentrated anchovy character, less salty and more refined than Asian fish sauces; descendant of Roman garum.', 'A few drops on spaghetti aglio-olio (Spaghetti alla Colatura — the canonical dish), drizzled on raw fish, in salad dressings, gratin glazes, premium pizza topping.', '["glass-bottle-50ml", "glass-bottle-100ml", "glass-bottle-250ml", "gift-pack-100ml"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Colatura", "Cetara fish sauce", "Italian colatura"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('3f290c37-23c0-faed-1594-ad9c38111772', 'IT', 'Italy', 'spices_salt_herbs', 'Sale Marino di Trapani IGP', '["Sale Marino di Trapani IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Sicilian sea salt from Trapani-Marsala lagoons, traditional shallow-pond solar evaporation. Bright crystalline white color, light flaky texture (or coarser depending on grind), characteristic delicate-mineral marine flavor with low bitter notes; among Italy''s premier artisan sea salts.', 'Finishing salt on grilled fish and meats, in raw fish service (carpaccio), on tomato salads with EVOO, in pasta water for premium preparations, salt-crust roasting, fleur-de-sel-style finishing.', '["paper-bag-coarse-1kg", "paper-bag-fine-1kg", "glass-jar-fine-200g", "ceramic-pot-flake-100g", "bulk-foodservice-25kg", "gift-pack-mixed-300g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Sale di Trapani", "Trapani sea salt", "Sicilian sea salt"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('ad591d63-c144-1241-6f7c-80b488339369', 'IT', 'Italy', 'spices_salt_herbs', 'Zafferano dell''Aquila DOP', '["Zafferano dell''Aquila DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Abruzzese saffron from Navelli plateau (L''Aquila province), traditional thread saffron from Crocus sativus. Deep ruby-red threads, intensely aromatic with characteristic floral-honey-hay notes, vivid yellow-orange color when infused; among the world''s premier saffrons (Iran-Spain-Italy triumvirate).', 'Risotto alla Milanese (canonical), seafood paella-style preparations, broths and stocks, golden infusions for desserts (saffron gelato, panna cotta), Abruzzese pasta dishes.', '["glass-vial-0.1g", "glass-vial-0.5g", "glass-vial-1g", "glass-jar-2g", "glass-jar-5g", "professional-bulk-10g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Zafferano dell''Aquila", "Navelli saffron"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('a5d7824a-6b70-ecc2-fb09-48a14b05757f', 'IT', 'Italy', 'spices_salt_herbs', 'Zafferano di San Gimignano DOP', '["Zafferano di San Gimignano DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Tuscan saffron from San Gimignano hills, traditional thread saffron with intense aromatic profile (slightly different from Aquilano — often described as more honeyed). Deep ruby-red threads, vivid coloring power.', 'Tuscan-style risotto, saffron-infused seafood preparations, golden desserts, paired with Vernaccia di San Gimignano wine in tasting menus.', '["glass-vial-0.1g", "glass-vial-0.5g", "glass-vial-1g", "glass-jar-2g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Zafferano sangimignanese", "San Gimignano saffron"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('a6c16496-c181-a7b1-9913-8121b9603ddb', 'IT', 'Italy', 'spices_salt_herbs', 'Zafferano di Sardegna DOP', '["Zafferano di Sardegna DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Sardinian saffron from Medio Campidano (San Gavino Monreale area). Deep red threads, intense aromatic profile, characteristic Mediterranean-floral notes.', 'Sardinian preparations — fregula con zafferano, malloreddus alla campidanese, seafood broths, infusions for sebadas variations.', '["glass-vial-0.1g", "glass-vial-0.5g", "glass-vial-1g", "glass-jar-2g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Zafferano sardo", "Sardinian saffron", "San Gavino saffron"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('ed9aeca3-cbb7-f6be-088c-de19fac137a6', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Aglio Bianco Polesano DOP', '["Aglio Bianco Polesano DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Veneto white garlic from Polesine plain (Rovigo province). Bright pearl-white bulbs with rosy-cream undertones, dense compact heads with 8-12 cloves, balanced spicy-sweet flavor, long storage life.', 'Foundation aromatic for Veneto cuisine — soffritto base, raw rubbed on bruschetta, garlic confit, roasted whole, classic in bagna cauda variations.', '["mesh-bag-1kg", "mesh-bag-3kg", "mesh-bag-5kg", "braided-treccia-500g", "braided-treccia-1kg", "retail-tray-300g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Aglio del Polesine", "Polesine white garlic"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('bcb392f1-210b-4871-ca3c-d3fa937846c9', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Aglio di Voghiera DOP', '["Aglio di Voghiera DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Emilian garlic from Voghiera area (Ferrara province), traditional Romagnolo cultivar. Pearly-white bulbs with cream-pink undertones, sweet-mild flavor with slight aromatic complexity.', 'Emilian cooking foundation, soffritto, raw applications, paired with regional cured meats.', '["mesh-bag-1kg", "mesh-bag-3kg", "braided-treccia-500g", "retail-tray-300g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Voghiera garlic"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('d432464c-ca53-785c-ed84-0edc0a22c003', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Aglio Rosso di Nubia (— this is a Slow Food Presidium, not EU IGP — see Layer 5)', '["Aglio Rosso di Nubia (— this is a Slow Food Presidium, not EU IGP — see Layer 5)"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, '', '', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, TRUE, 'L2'),
  ('c4a9dc92-3054-7f5d-e55d-32705a76a199', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Asparago Bianco di Bassano DOP', '["Asparago Bianco di Bassano DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Veneto white asparagus from Bassano del Grappa, Common Bianco di Bassano variety. Tender ivory spears with delicate sweet-bitter balance, fine fibrous texture; harvested before sun exposure to prevent chlorophyll formation.', 'Classic preparation "alla Bassanese" with hard-boiled egg, EVOO and vinegar; risotto with asparagus; lasagne; spring tasting menus paired with Vespaiolo wine.', '["crate-5kg", "crate-10kg", "retail-bunch-500g", "retail-bunch-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[3, 4, 5, 6]'::jsonb, '["Asparago Bianco Bassano", "Bassano white asparagus"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('6bfb6a3a-27ce-1e66-6467-c2ae48093d37', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Asparago Bianco di Cimadolmo IGP', '["Asparago Bianco di Cimadolmo IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Veneto white asparagus from Cimadolmo area (Treviso province), traditional white-blanched cultivation. Tender white spears with subtle sweet-bitter profile.', 'Spring service Veneto-style with egg and vinaigrette, in risotto, salads with prosciutto.', '["crate-5kg", "retail-bunch-500g", "retail-bunch-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[3, 4, 5, 6]'::jsonb, '["Cimadolmo asparagus"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('72f4aa51-d0ed-bcdd-bcc1-f81e59f7b3cb', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Asparago di Badoere IGP', '["Asparago di Badoere IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Veneto asparagus from Badoere area (Treviso province), both white and green varieties. Spring delicacy with characteristic Veneto profile.', 'Spring tasting menus, classic Veneto pairings.', '["crate-5kg", "retail-bunch-500g"]'::jsonb, '[3, 4, 5, 6]'::jsonb, '["Badoere asparagus"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('844c061a-094b-8397-ad1d-b465d88098a6', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Asparago di Cantello IGP', '["Asparago di Cantello IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Lombard asparagus from Cantello area (Varese province), traditional spring vegetable.', 'Lombard spring dishes — risotto, frittata, antipasto.', '["crate-5kg", "retail-bunch-500g"]'::jsonb, '[3, 4, 5, 6]'::jsonb, '["Cantello asparagus"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('3508805b-98fc-87ee-ca18-9894e4373b6e', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Asparago Verde di Altedo IGP', '["Asparago Verde di Altedo IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Emilian green asparagus from Altedo area (Bologna province). Bright green spears with characteristic flavor profile, traditional Emilian variety.', 'Emilian spring dishes — pasta, risotto, classic with Parmigiano shavings.', '["crate-5kg", "retail-bunch-500g"]'::jsonb, '[3, 4, 5, 6]'::jsonb, '["Altedo asparagus"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('ad91a638-1d21-229d-6539-5a9b2d29dac1', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Carciofo Brindisino IGP', '["Carciofo Brindisino IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Apulian artichoke from Brindisi area, "Brindisino" variety. Medium-large green-violet heads, tender flesh, balanced bitter-sweet flavor.', 'Apulian spring preparations — alla giudia (fried whole), in pasta and rice, raw thinly sliced for carpaccio salads.', '["crate-5kg", "crate-10kg", "retail-bunch-500g"]'::jsonb, '[11, 12, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5]'::jsonb, '["Brindisi artichoke"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('48cf6dea-0b45-b504-e305-e88a6b764517', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Carciofo di Paestum IGP', '["Carciofo di Paestum IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Campanian artichoke from Paestum plain (Salerno province), Tondo di Paestum variety. Round green-violet heads, tender heart, sweet flavor with delicate bitter notes.', 'Campanian preparations — alla romana (braised with mint), grilled, in pasta and seafood preparations.', '["crate-5kg", "retail-bunch-500g"]'::jsonb, '[3, 4, 5, 6]'::jsonb, '["Tondo di Paestum"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('e66bacb4-6509-ff8e-baf5-fef312465b8c', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Carciofo Romanesco del Lazio IGP', '["Carciofo Romanesco del Lazio IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Lazio Roman artichoke (Romanesco/Mammola variety). Large round green-violet heads, tender heart, distinctive sweet flavor with low bitter notes — the iconic Roman artichoke.', 'Carciofi alla giudia (deep-fried whole — Roman-Jewish classic), alla romana (braised with mint and garlic — Roman classic), in salads, pasta sauces.', '["crate-5kg", "retail-bunch-500g", "single-large-tray-300g"]'::jsonb, '[2, 3, 4, 5, 6]'::jsonb, '["Mammola", "Romanesco", "Roman artichoke"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('715cd80f-fb1c-d837-b134-d88df341c11b', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Carciofo Spinoso di Sardegna DOP', '["Carciofo Spinoso di Sardegna DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Sardinian spiny artichoke, distinctive elongated shape with thorny bracts. Tender flesh, intense aromatic flavor with notes of fresh herbs and cardoon.', 'Sardinian preparations — alla griglia, in agrodolce, with fregula, in autumn-spring tasting menus paired with Cannonau.', '["crate-5kg", "retail-bunch-500g"]'::jsonb, '[11, 12, 1, 2, 3, 4]'::jsonb, '["Spinoso sardo", "Sardinian spiny artichoke"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('09ad80ba-0ad2-4466-bc8b-c35ec0c6d611', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Cardoncello di Murgia (— not EU registered — Slow Food Presidium, see Layer 5)', '["Cardoncello di Murgia (— not EU registered — Slow Food Presidium, see Layer 5)"]'::jsonb, 'OTHER', '["OTHER"]'::jsonb, '', '', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, TRUE, 'L2'),
  ('06baae7d-1a6d-62f2-0450-25cdc37d4362', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Cipolla Bianca di Margherita IGP', '["Cipolla Bianca di Margherita IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Apulian white onion from Margherita di Savoia (Foggia province). Pearly-white bulbs, crisp tender flesh, sweet-mild flavor with delicate piquancy, low pungency.', 'Raw in salads, marinated for antipasto, classic in Apulian focaccia, sweet-and-sour preparations.', '["crate-10kg", "mesh-bag-3kg", "mesh-bag-5kg", "retail-tray-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9]'::jsonb, '["Cipolla bianca di Margherita di Savoia", "Margherita onion"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('bb0784ef-5e45-b568-aa75-06433e3ff3c6', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Cipolla Rossa di Tropea Calabria IGP', '["Cipolla Rossa di Tropea Calabria IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Calabrian red onion from Tropea coast, distinctive elongated bulb with deep purple-red color and white inner flesh. Distinctively sweet-mild flavor with very low pungency, high sugar content; one of Italy''s most prized onions.', 'Raw in salads (especially with bread, tuna, oranges), caramelized for tarts, in agrodolce preparations, jam-marmalade for cheese boards, Calabrian focaccia.', '["crate-10kg", "braided-treccia-500g", "braided-treccia-1kg", "retail-net-bag-1kg", "marmalade-jar-100g"]'::jsonb, '[4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10]'::jsonb, '["Cipolla di Tropea", "Tropea red onion", "Cipolla rossa calabrese"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('f8b293eb-60cb-dd39-9439-d1a088868bbe', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Fagiolo Cannellino di Atina DOP', '["Fagiolo Cannellino di Atina DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Lazio white kidney bean from Atina valley (Frosinone province). Small ivory bean with thin skin, creamy tender texture, delicate sweet flavor.', 'Lazio bean preparations — pasta e fagioli, sauteed with sage and garlic, in soups; less mealy than commercial cannellini.', '["vacuum-pack-dried-500g", "vacuum-pack-dried-1kg", "glass-jar-cooked-300g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Cannellino di Atina"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('9d27b6a1-e8a3-942a-187b-87491e3f4bb1', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Fagiolo Cuneo IGP', '["Fagiolo Cuneo IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Piedmontese bean variety (multiple types — Bianco di Bagnasco, Borlotto di Cuneo etc.) from Cuneo province. Distinctive flavors per variety, generally creamy texture, balanced earthy-sweet profile.', 'Piedmontese pasta and rice dishes, soups, paired with mountain cheeses and salumi.', '["vacuum-pack-dried-500g", "vacuum-pack-dried-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Cuneo bean"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('d760369b-1fda-4cc5-04ae-0fd360599fa7', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Fagiolo di Lamon della Vallata Bellunese IGP', '["Fagiolo di Lamon della Vallata Bellunese IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Veneto bean from Lamon valley (Belluno province), four traditional varieties (Spagnolit, Spagnol, Calonega, Canalino). Distinctive plump shape, creamy texture, intensely flavored with characteristic chestnut-earthy notes.', 'Pasta e fagioli alla veneta (canonical), in Veneto soups, paired with regional cured meats and polenta.', '["vacuum-pack-dried-500g", "vacuum-pack-dried-1kg", "gift-pack-300g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Fagiolo di Lamon", "Lamon bean"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('aeaf5af4-baba-1152-35a6-3d8eba4e9020', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Fagiolo di Sarconi IGP', '["Fagiolo di Sarconi IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Lucanian bean from Sarconi area (Potenza province), multiple traditional varieties. Distinctive flavor with characteristic earthy-sweet notes, tender texture.', 'Lucanian preparations — minestre, with peperoni cruschi, in regional pasta dishes.', '["vacuum-pack-dried-500g", "vacuum-pack-dried-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Sarconi bean"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('2f9ff8e2-1d7e-5be5-d2d3-9a9efbb415d8', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Fagiolo di Sorana IGP', '["Fagiolo di Sorana IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Tuscan bean from Sorana valley (Pistoia province), Piattellino variety. Small flat ivory bean, tender thin-skinned, delicate sweet flavor.', 'Tuscan preparations — fagioli all''olio, in zuppa di farro, with cured meats.', '["vacuum-pack-dried-250g", "vacuum-pack-dried-500g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Sorana bean", "Piattellino"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('c75225ec-d5f9-040b-0874-a0456bf96449', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Farro della Garfagnana IGP', '["Farro della Garfagnana IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Tuscan emmer wheat from Garfagnana valley (Lucca province), traditional Triticum dicoccum. Distinctive nutty earthy flavor, chewy firm texture, retains shape after long cooking — Italy''s premier farro.', 'Zuppa di farro alla garfagnina (canonical), farro salads, risotto-style farrotto, in pasta dishes, paired with mountain cheeses.', '["vacuum-pack-500g", "vacuum-pack-1kg", "gift-pack-300g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Farro Garfagnana", "Garfagnana emmer"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('5970238b-665f-d83a-a1a4-8e72757d4230', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Farro di Monteleone di Spoleto DOP', '["Farro di Monteleone di Spoleto DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Umbrian emmer wheat from Monteleone di Spoleto (Perugia province), traditional Triticum dicoccum. Distinctive nutty flavor, chewy texture, characteristic Umbrian profile.', 'Umbrian preparations — minestra di farro, salads, paired with regional cheeses and truffles.', '["vacuum-pack-500g", "vacuum-pack-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Monteleone farro"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('139189eb-7923-8ed0-0f07-cffeed7c1138', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Insalata di Lusia IGP', '["Insalata di Lusia IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Veneto salad greens from Lusia area (Rovigo province), Cappuccia and Gentile varieties. Crisp tender leaves, balanced sweet-mild flavor, bright clean character.', 'Premium fresh salad service, accompaniment for antipasto, in mixed salads with regional ingredients.', '["crate-5kg", "retail-tray-200g", "retail-tray-300g"]'::jsonb, '[3, 4, 5, 6, 9, 10, 11]'::jsonb, '["Lusia salad"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('d395ac49-2544-e49f-bebd-08d5e9cae29a', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Lenticchia di Castelluccio di Norcia IGP', '["Lenticchia di Castelluccio di Norcia IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Umbrian lentil from Castelluccio di Norcia plateau (Sibillini mountains), small distinctive multi-color lentil (mottled green-brown). Thin skin, delicate sweet-earthy flavor, tender quick-cooking texture, holds shape after cooking — Italy''s most prized lentil.', 'Lentils with Cotechino/Zampone (New Year''s classic), Umbrian soups, in pasta dishes, paired with truffle and Norcia salumi.', '["vacuum-pack-500g", "vacuum-pack-1kg", "gift-pack-300g", "professional-bulk-5kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Lenticchia di Castelluccio", "Castelluccio lentil", "Castelluccio di Norcia lentil"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('274cd301-1cb4-d9ae-e780-a0a17321e4c4', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Marrone di Serino IGP (this is a chestnut IGP — moved to fruits_nuts; here a placeholder note)', '["Marrone di Serino IGP (this is a chestnut IGP — moved to fruits_nuts; here a placeholder note)"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, '', '', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, TRUE, 'L2'),
