  ('dfa5345f-1ae8-22f5-68fc-829c9e346e27', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Pane di Altamura DOP', '["Pane di Altamura DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Apulian sourdough bread from Altamura (Bari province), Senatore Cappelli durum wheat semolina. Distinctive thick golden crust, dense moist amber crumb, intensely aromatic with toasted-cereal notes, exceptional shelf life (5-7 days).', 'Apulian table bread, bruschetta base, panzanella alla pugliese, leftover-bread cucina povera dishes (acquasale), classic with EVOO and tomato.', '["whole-loaf-1kg", "whole-loaf-2kg", "half-loaf-vacuum-500g", "sliced-vacuum-300g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Pane di Altamura", "Altamura bread"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('73fa10b7-7b37-3a1f-c7af-0c7f4fc22ccc', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Pane di Matera IGP', '["Pane di Matera IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Lucanian sourdough bread from Matera (Sassi caves bread tradition), traditional durum wheat semolina. Distinctive horn shape (cornetto), thick crust, dense amber-yellow crumb, intense toasted-cereal aroma.', 'Lucanian table bread, paired with local cured meats and pecorino, in cucina povera preparations, bruschetta base.', '["whole-loaf-1kg", "whole-loaf-2kg", "sliced-vacuum-300g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Pane di Matera", "Matera bread"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('9893172a-da65-5071-b71f-5804c166dc5d', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Patata della Sila IGP', '["Patata della Sila IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Calabrian potato from Sila plateau (high mountain agriculture). Yellow-fleshed potato with characteristic floury texture, balanced earthy-sweet flavor, holds shape after cooking.', 'Calabrian preparations — gnocchi, mountain stews, paired with peperoncino and ''nduja.', '["mesh-bag-2kg", "mesh-bag-5kg", "mesh-bag-10kg", "crate-25kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Patate della Sila"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('ef075194-9407-4179-dddb-a5b35840dce7', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Patata di Bologna DOP', '["Patata di Bologna DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Emilian potato from Bologna area, Primura variety. Yellow flesh, balanced cooking texture, classic table potato.', 'Emilian gnocchi (preferred), tortelli filling, side dish, mashed.', '["mesh-bag-2kg", "mesh-bag-5kg", "crate-25kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Patata Bologna"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('3e70f635-b099-5a56-83e0-ec5e1df59eda', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Patata novella di Galatina DOP', '["Patata novella di Galatina DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Apulian new potato from Galatina (Lecce province), Sieglinde variety. Small thin-skinned new potatoes, tender flesh, delicate sweet flavor.', 'Roasted whole, in spring-summer Apulian preparations, salads, paired with seafood.', '["crate-5kg", "mesh-bag-2kg", "retail-tray-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[4, 5, 6]'::jsonb, '["Patata novella Galatina"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('b76e7a84-f2c1-38ee-7ebb-a60795210a8e', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Patata Rossa di Colfiorito IGP', '["Patata Rossa di Colfiorito IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Umbrian-Marchigiana red-skinned potato from Colfiorito plateau, traditional mountain cultivar. Yellow flesh, distinctive earthy-sweet flavor, firm texture.', 'Umbrian preparations — gnocchi, mountain stews, roasted with herbs, paired with Castelluccio lentils.', '["mesh-bag-2kg", "mesh-bag-5kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Patata rossa Colfiorito"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('5cac6da6-bab7-df0a-3908-96afa468fcf9', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Peperone di Pontecorvo DOP', '["Peperone di Pontecorvo DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Lazio sweet pepper from Pontecorvo area (Frosinone province), traditional elongated pepper. Bright red, thick fleshy walls, very sweet mild flavor.', 'Roasted and peeled for antipasto, stuffed (peperoni ripieni), in peperonata, raw in salads, marinated for preserves.', '["crate-5kg", "crate-10kg", "retail-tray-500g"]'::jsonb, '[7, 8, 9, 10]'::jsonb, '["Peperone Pontecorvo"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('2504fbd7-b498-31eb-c6b2-517a353aad16', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Peperone di Senise IGP', '["Peperone di Senise IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Lucanian dried sweet pepper from Senise area, distinctive elongated red pepper traditionally air-dried then fried (peperoni cruschi — "crispy peppers"). Crisp paper-thin texture when fried, intensely sweet-savory flavor with toasted notes; iconic Lucanian product.', 'Peperoni cruschi as garnish on pasta (with Pecorino di Filiano, Lucanica), as antipasto, crumbled on baccalà, in regional rustic preparations; ground into traditional Lucanian sweet paprika.', '["dried-bunch-200g", "dried-bunch-500g", "fried-vacuum-100g", "fried-vacuum-200g", "ground-paprika-jar-100g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Peperone crusco", "Peperoni di Senise", "Crusco"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('8dc76475-2faa-c1dc-8cc4-f7155ff526aa', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Pomodorino del Piennolo del Vesuvio DOP', '["Pomodorino del Piennolo del Vesuvio DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Campanian small cherry tomato from Vesuvius slopes, traditional "piennolo" hanging-bunch storage. Small bright-red tomato with thick skin, intensely concentrated sweet-tart-savory flavor with characteristic mineral-volcanic notes, exceptional storage (months).', 'Pasta and pizza topping (especially Campanian classics), in seafood pasta, raw in summer salads, oven-confit, in jars as conserva.', '["fresh-bunch-piennolo-500g", "fresh-bunch-piennolo-1kg", "glass-jar-conserva-500g", "glass-jar-conserva-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[7, 8, 9, 10, 11, 12, 1]'::jsonb, '["Pomodorino Piennolo", "Piennolo del Vesuvio", "Vesuvius cherry tomato"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('a4924533-cdfc-8260-8e78-10b9c32c0f56', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Pomodoro di Pachino IGP', '["Pomodoro di Pachino IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Sicilian tomato from Pachino area (Siracusa province), four varieties (Ciliegino, Costoluto, Tondo Liscio, Grappolo). Distinctive intense sweet flavor with characteristic Mediterranean profile.', 'Premium fresh service, on caprese, in pasta with seafood, in caponata variations, oven-confit.', '["crate-5kg", "crate-10kg", "retail-tray-500g", "retail-tray-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Pachino tomato", "Ciliegino di Pachino"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('4d4b0f95-a10c-12dc-4abb-a6dcf66e260a', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Pomodoro S. Marzano dell''Agro Sarnese-Nocerino DOP', '["Pomodoro S. Marzano dell''Agro Sarnese-Nocerino DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Campanian elongated plum tomato from Sarno-Nocera plain, traditional San Marzano variety. Distinctive elongated shape, deep red color, thick flesh with low water content, balanced sweet-acid flavor with concentrated tomato character — the iconic pizza tomato.', 'Pizza Napoletana sauce (canonical), Neapolitan ragù, pasta sauces (pomarola), San Marzano in scatola is benchmark for Italian tomato cuisine globally.', '["glass-jar-whole-peeled-400g", "can-whole-peeled-400g", "can-whole-peeled-2.5kg", "can-whole-peeled-3kg", "fresh-crate-5kg"]'::jsonb, '[7, 8, 9]'::jsonb, '["San Marzano DOP", "San Marzano dell''Agro Sarnese-Nocerino", "San Marzano tomato"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('76cffc5c-5e50-a638-995f-95683831c348', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Radicchio di Chioggia IGP', '["Radicchio di Chioggia IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Veneto radicchio from Chioggia area, distinctive round red-and-white tight-headed variety. Crisp leaves with characteristic bitter-sweet flavor, less complex than Treviso varieties but more widely available.', 'Veneto salads, grilled, in risotto, mixed salads.', '["crate-5kg", "crate-10kg", "single-head-300-500g", "retail-tray-500g"]'::jsonb, '[9, 10, 11, 12, 1, 2, 3]'::jsonb, '["Chioggia radicchio"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('c8eef159-664b-f89f-c710-e3ade2ab36c6', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Radicchio di Verona IGP', '["Radicchio di Verona IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Veneto radicchio from Verona area, two types (Precoce harvested early autumn, Tardivo harvested late winter). Distinctive shape and bitter-sweet character.', 'Veneto salads, grilled, in risotto.', '["crate-5kg", "single-head-300g", "retail-tray-500g"]'::jsonb, '[9, 10, 11, 12, 1, 2, 3]'::jsonb, '["Verona radicchio"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('fbd9b729-4fc3-bd7d-28c0-8792f4bb2c11', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Radicchio Rosso di Treviso IGP', '["Radicchio Rosso di Treviso IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Veneto radicchio from Treviso area, two iconic types: Precoce (early, October-November, broader head) and Tardivo (late, December-March, distinctive narrow elongated leaves with white ribs and dark-red tips). Tardivo undergoes "imbianchimento" (water-darkness blanching) producing premium product. Bittersweet complex flavor, crisp tender texture; among Italy''s most prized winter vegetables.', 'Risotto al radicchio (Veneto classic), grilled with EVOO and salt, in salads with Gorgonzola and walnuts, in pasta with sausage and cream, raw thinly sliced for tasting menus; classic with Recioto and Amarone wines.', '["crate-5kg", "single-head-300-500g", "retail-tray-500g", "gift-pack-Tardivo-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[10, 11, 12, 1, 2, 3]'::jsonb, '["Radicchio di Treviso", "Treviso radicchio", "Radicchio Rosso Tardivo", "Treviso Tardivo"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('eed2cdb8-b672-89ae-d53a-df18921fc722', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Radicchio Variegato di Castelfranco IGP', '["Radicchio Variegato di Castelfranco IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Veneto radicchio from Castelfranco area, distinctive open-rosette form with white-cream leaves splashed in red-purple variegation — known as "edible flower" for visual elegance. Mild bittersweet flavor, very tender crisp texture.', 'Premium salads (especially as decorative element), risotto, paired with persimmon and pomegranate in winter menus, on cheese boards.', '["crate-5kg", "single-head-300-500g", "retail-tray-500g", "gift-pack-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[11, 12, 1, 2]'::jsonb, '["Variegato di Castelfranco", "Castelfranco radicchio", "Edible flower radicchio"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('d2b23f39-5080-a94e-69c3-374b43f1dfaf', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Sedano Bianco di Sperlonga IGP', '["Sedano Bianco di Sperlonga IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Lazio white celery from Sperlonga area (Latina province), traditional blanched celery. Tender crisp white-pale-green stalks, delicate sweet flavor with low bitter notes.', 'Raw in pinzimonio (with EVOO and salt — Roman classic), in soffritto, in mixed salads, with anchovy bagna cauda.', '["crate-5kg", "retail-bunch-500g", "retail-bunch-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[10, 11, 12, 1, 2, 3, 4]'::jsonb, '["Sedano Sperlonga"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('941c173f-7783-4dd1-41ab-6ed194e051aa', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Marrone di Serino IGP', '["Marrone di Serino IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Campanian chestnut from Serino area (Avellino province) — note this entry properly belongs in fruits_nuts and may have been listed there. Large mahogany shell, sweet flesh.', 'Caldarroste, candied, in Campanian autumn cuisine.', '["crate-10kg", "vacuum-pack-cooked-500g"]'::jsonb, '[10, 11, 12]'::jsonb, '["Marrone Serino"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('cda5b135-9c8b-bec0-0b34-e3226bdcecc1', 'IT', 'Italy', 'rice_pasta_grains', 'Cappellacci di Zucca Ferraresi IGP', '["Cappellacci di Zucca Ferraresi IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Emilian filled fresh pasta from Ferrara, distinctive hat-shape stuffed with butternut squash, Parmigiano, nutmeg, breadcrumbs. Tender egg-pasta wrapper, sweet-savory squash filling with characteristic Renaissance-style spicing.', 'Served with butter and sage, with ragù bianco, with Parmigiano shavings; signature Ferrarese restaurant primo.', '["vacuum-pack-fresh-250g", "vacuum-pack-fresh-500g", "frozen-bulk-1kg", "frozen-bulk-3kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Cappellacci di Ferrara", "Pumpkin cappellacci"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('6e472778-9055-5546-49a0-7f4362cc9e0f', 'IT', 'Italy', 'rice_pasta_grains', 'Coppia Ferrarese IGP', '["Coppia Ferrarese IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Emilian bread from Ferrara, distinctive twisted-horn shape (two ribbons joined). Crisp crackly thin crust, dense compact crumb, characteristic intense crust-to-crumb ratio.', 'Ferrarese table bread, paired with Salama da sugo IGP and regional cured meats; visually distinctive in bread baskets.', '["loose-piece-150-200g", "retail-pack-3-piece-500g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Coppia di Ferrara", "Ferrara twin bread"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('ea41d7d8-0537-3f7d-4321-93b0e3dec14f', 'IT', 'Italy', 'rice_pasta_grains', 'Maccheroncini di Campofilone IGP', '["Maccheroncini di Campofilone IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Marchigiana fresh egg pasta from Campofilone (Fermo province), distinctive ultra-thin square strands hand-cut from egg-rich dough. Delicate texture, intensely eggy flavor, traditional with rich ragù.', 'Maccheroncini al ragù marchigiano (canonical), with seafood, with truffle, in regional fine dining.', '["dried-vacuum-250g", "dried-vacuum-500g", "fresh-vacuum-250g", "fresh-vacuum-500g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Campofilone", "Maccheroncini Campofilone"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('17aecb2b-ba44-112f-53c2-0a74df7175ac', 'IT', 'Italy', 'rice_pasta_grains', 'Pasta di Gragnano IGP', '["Pasta di Gragnano IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Campanian dried pasta from Gragnano (Naples area), traditional bronze-die extruded pasta from durum wheat semolina, slow low-temperature dried. Rough porous textured surface, golden color, holds sauce excellently, al dente bite — the global benchmark for premium dried pasta.', 'Italian and international fine dining — every shape (spaghetti, paccheri, ziti, candele, fusilli, mezze maniche etc.); essential for premium pasta service in restaurants and gourmet retail.', '["retail-bag-500g", "retail-bag-1kg", "foodservice-bag-3kg", "foodservice-bag-5kg", "gift-pack-multi-shape-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Pasta Gragnano", "Gragnano pasta", "Bronze-die Gragnano"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('4bc042fb-2fd5-ca0f-85e9-1929ac234569', 'IT', 'Italy', 'rice_pasta_grains', 'Pizza Napoletana STG', '["Pizza Napoletana STG"]'::jsonb, 'TSG', '["TSG"]'::jsonb, 'Neapolitan pizza specification (Specialità Tradizionale Garantita, not place-of-origin). Two canonical types: Marinara (tomato, garlic, oregano, EVOO) and Margherita (tomato, mozzarella di bufala or fior di latte, basil, EVOO). Distinctive thin soft pliable crust with charred leopard-spotted cornicione, slightly wet center, tomato-forward flavor.', 'Restaurant pizza service following STG specification (wood-fired oven 485°C, 60-90 second cook); training certification for "Vera Pizza Napoletana" pizzerias globally.', '["Not a packaged product — restaurant preparation specification. Iriska commercial relevance is the certification standard", "not a tradable SKU. Recommend Layer 3/4 exclude from product catalog."]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Vera Pizza Napoletana", "Neapolitan pizza", "VPN"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('994831d4-cb16-2551-1dca-059644f78521', 'IT', 'Italy', 'rice_pasta_grains', 'Riso del Delta del Po IGP', '["Riso del Delta del Po IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Veneto/Emilia rice from Po delta, traditional varieties (Carnaroli, Arborio, Volano, Baldo). Distinctive starch profile suited for risotto, characteristic delta-water mineral notes.', 'Risotto base (especially with seafood given coastal context), in soups, classic with Cozza di Scardovari DOP.', '["vacuum-pack-1kg", "vacuum-pack-5kg", "foodservice-bag-25kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Riso Po Delta", "Po delta rice"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('ed11c48b-8cac-7727-f05e-1a625df0f6ad', 'IT', 'Italy', 'rice_pasta_grains', 'Riso di Baraggia Biellese e Vercellese DOP', '["Riso di Baraggia Biellese e Vercellese DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Piedmontese rice from Baraggia plateau (Biella-Vercelli provinces), multiple varieties (Arborio, Carnaroli, Baldo, Sant''Andrea, Balilla). Distinctive starch and grain profile, traditional risotto rice.', 'Premium risotto rice (Carnaroli especially prized), risotto alla milanese, in Piedmontese classics.', '["vacuum-pack-1kg", "vacuum-pack-5kg", "foodservice-bag-25kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Riso Baraggia", "Baraggia rice"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('5996c6e6-5304-3bf9-8f69-62faf8430d14', 'IT', 'Italy', 'rice_pasta_grains', 'Riso Nano Vialone Veronese IGP', '["Riso Nano Vialone Veronese IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Veneto rice from Verona area, traditional Vialone Nano semifino variety. Distinctive small round grain, exceptional starch release for risotto, traditional Veneto risotto rice (preferred over Arborio in regional cooking).', 'Risi e bisi (Veneto classic), risotto al radicchio, risotto al pesce di lago, risotto all''isolana — Veneto risotto base of choice.', '["vacuum-pack-1kg", "vacuum-pack-5kg", "foodservice-bag-25kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Vialone Nano Veronese", "Veronese vialone"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('94f856a8-3c39-eaef-2f58-52b541443915', 'IT', 'Italy', 'rice_pasta_grains', 'Pizzoccheri della Valtellina IGP', '["Pizzoccheri della Valtellina IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Lombard pasta from Valtellina, distinctive flat tagliatelle of buckwheat-and-wheat flour. Earthy nutty flavor from buckwheat, denser chewier texture than wheat pasta.', 'Pizzoccheri alla valtellinese (canonical) — boiled with potatoes and savoy cabbage, layered with Valtellina Casera DOP and butter-garlic-sage; quintessential Alpine winter dish.', '["dried-vacuum-250g", "dried-vacuum-500g", "fresh-vacuum-300g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Pizzoccheri Valtellinese", "Valtellina pizzoccheri"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('aaf8d663-83a4-fdf0-c9da-90644b47a03b', 'IT', 'Italy', 'rice_pasta_grains', 'Piadina Romagnola IGP', '["Piadina Romagnola IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Romagnolo flatbread (round thin unleavened flour-water-fat bread). Two styles — Riminese (thinner, more pliable) and Forli-Cesenatico (thicker). Soft when fresh-warmed, slightly crisp surface, mild flour-and-fat flavor.', 'Folded around Squacquerone di Romagna DOP and prosciutto crudo (canonical filling); also with rocket and stracchino, with Mortadella, with sausage; quintessential Romagnolo street food and casual restaurant base.', '["vacuum-pack-fresh-3-piece-300g", "vacuum-pack-fresh-5-piece-500g", "frozen-bulk-2kg", "foodservice-frozen-50-piece"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Piadina", "Piada", "Piadina riminese", "Cassone (filled folded variant)"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('97a489ff-f591-e14d-9ea3-8b6de023a070', 'IT', 'Italy', 'rice_pasta_grains', 'Tortellini di Bologna (— not EU registered, traditional product — see Layer 5)', '["Tortellini di Bologna (— not EU registered, traditional product — see Layer 5)"]'::jsonb, 'OTHER', '["OTHER"]'::jsonb, '', '', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, TRUE, 'L2'),
  ('6700091e-f624-ffc7-0f49-0bda6d8d7036', 'IT', 'Italy', 'rice_pasta_grains', 'Pane di Tortone (— not currently registered — placeholder)', '["Pane di Tortone (— not currently registered — placeholder)"]'::jsonb, 'OTHER', '["OTHER"]'::jsonb, '', '', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, TRUE, 'L2'),
  ('9007c7a5-bebd-e7b9-5b8d-ae77a777e495', 'IT', 'Italy', 'rice_pasta_grains', 'Bruschetta di Lariano (— not registered — see Layer 5)', '["Bruschetta di Lariano (— not registered — see Layer 5)"]'::jsonb, 'OTHER', '["OTHER"]'::jsonb, '', '', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, TRUE, 'L2'),
  ('ffd3f23c-c286-66c8-6537-6073ae9a76f2', 'IT', 'Italy', 'rice_pasta_grains', 'Pane di Genzano IGP', '["Pane di Genzano IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Lazio sourdough bread from Genzano area (Castelli Romani, Rome province), traditional wheat bread with bran-dusted crust. Characteristic dark crackly crust, dense moist crumb, intensely aromatic with sourdough-fermented notes.', 'Roman table bread, bruschetta base, panzanella, accompaniment for Lazio salumi and pecorino.', '["whole-loaf-1kg", "whole-loaf-2kg", "half-loaf-vacuum-500g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Pane Genzano", "Genzano bread"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('1a645351-6415-044b-cffb-698261049bf2', 'IT', 'Italy', 'rice_pasta_grains', 'Riso del Po Delta IGP', '["Riso del Po Delta IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, '', '', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, TRUE, 'L2'),
  ('281756a5-57c7-ddce-6c8f-1592ac4c93a4', 'IT', 'Italy', 'rice_pasta_grains', 'Riso Piacentino IGP (if registered)', '["Riso Piacentino IGP (if registered)"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, '', '', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, TRUE, 'L2'),
  ('c3ddf31c-0795-71db-0f80-a8641a92ea2c', 'IT', 'Italy', 'rice_pasta_grains', 'Bottarga di Tonno (— not currently registered as DOP', '["Bottarga di Tonno (— not currently registered as DOP", "IGP)"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO", "PGI"]'::jsonb, '', '', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, TRUE, 'L2'),
  ('6a636f14-8e92-e7e3-40eb-850caa147087', 'IT', 'Italy', 'rice_pasta_grains', 'Riso Nano Vialone Veronese IGP — *already described above*', '["Riso Nano Vialone Veronese IGP — *already described above*"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, '', '', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, TRUE, 'L2'),
  ('5688d7b5-343d-7b3c-4f14-e2c29d1d8ecb', 'IT', 'Italy', 'rice_pasta_grains', 'Pizza Napoletana STG — *already described above*', '["Pizza Napoletana STG — *already described above*"]'::jsonb, 'TSG', '["TSG"]'::jsonb, '', '', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, TRUE, 'L2'),
  ('a84f9884-9afa-650a-b75d-23d1c561ac17', 'IT', 'Italy', 'honey_sweeteners', 'Miele della Lunigiana DOP', '["Miele della Lunigiana DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Tuscan honey from Lunigiana mountains (Massa-Carrara province), two main varieties — Acacia (very pale gold, delicate vanilla-floral) and Castagno (chestnut, dark amber, bitter-aromatic woody profile). Both produced in Lunigiana valleys.', 'Acacia drizzled on Pecorino Toscano DOP, in tea, on yogurt; Castagno paired with aged cheeses (especially Pecorino delle Balze Volterrane DOP), in salad dressings, on roasted meats.', '["glass-jar-250g", "glass-jar-500g", "glass-jar-1kg", "gift-pack-multi-variety-300g", "foodservice-bulk-3kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Miele Lunigiana", "Lunigiana honey"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('5f030ba8-51d6-6d7c-6cc7-af284ad6384a', 'IT', 'Italy', 'honey_sweeteners', 'Miele delle Dolomiti Bellunesi DOP', '["Miele delle Dolomiti Bellunesi DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Veneto honey from Dolomite mountains (Belluno province), six varieties (Acacia, Tiglio/Linden, Millefiori, Castagno, Tarassaco/Dandelion, Rododendro/Rhododendron). Each variety distinctive — Rhododendron pale and floral, Linden medium-amber with mint notes, Millefiori complex multi-flower profile.', 'Variety-specific pairings — Acacia on Trentino cheeses, Rhododendron on yogurt and panna cotta, Castagno on aged cheese, Linden in tea and on Trentino strudel.', '["glass-jar-250g", "glass-jar-500g", "glass-jar-1kg", "gift-pack-multi-variety-300g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Miele Dolomiti Bellunesi", "Dolomite honey"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('a5d383b6-e2ca-9564-3f6a-87b668439c9a', 'IT', 'Italy', 'honey_sweeteners', 'Miele Varesino DOP', '["Miele Varesino DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Lombard honey from Varese area (Lake Varese-Lake Maggiore zone), Acacia variety predominant. Pale gold, very delicate vanilla-floral flavor, fluid liquid texture (low crystallization).', 'Drizzled on cheese (especially fresh goat cheeses like Formaggella del Luinese DOP), in tea, on yogurt, in salad dressings.', '["glass-jar-250g", "glass-jar-500g", "glass-jar-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Miele Varese", "Varese honey"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('39741e11-3b1f-da5a-285c-4f7205e6bc74', 'IT', 'Italy', 'sweets_pastry_confectionery', 'Cantuccini Toscani IGP', '["Cantuccini Toscani IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Tuscan twice-baked almond biscuits, traditional Prato origin. Pale golden color, very crunchy hard texture, sweet flavor with intense almond notes, balanced with vanilla. Designed for dipping in Vin Santo.', 'Classic Tuscan dessert service — served with Vin Santo for end-of-meal dipping; also paired with sweet wines, espresso, cheese course; stocked as ambient gift item.', '["retail-bag-200g", "retail-bag-400g", "gift-pack-tin-300g", "gift-pack-box-500g", "foodservice-bulk-3kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Cantucci", "Biscotti di Prato", "Tuscan cantucci"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('ecd6881b-9410-18a4-ba78-e10dd4b98ccd', 'IT', 'Italy', 'sweets_pastry_confectionery', 'Pampepato di Terni IGP', '["Pampepato di Terni IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Umbrian Christmas spiced cake from Terni, dense round cake with chocolate, candied fruit, almonds, hazelnuts, walnuts, pine nuts, raisins, honey, cocoa, cinnamon, nutmeg, pepper. Intensely complex sweet-spiced flavor, dense moist texture, traditional Renaissance-origin Christmas dolce.', 'Christmas dessert service in Umbrian restaurants, on cheese boards as sweet pairing, sliced with Vin Santo or Sagrantino Passito; gift packaging for ambient retail.', '["whole-cake-300g-gift-box", "whole-cake-500g-gift-box", "whole-cake-800g-gift-box", "sliced-vacuum-200g"]'::jsonb, '[11, 12]'::jsonb, '["Pampapato", "Panpepato", "Pampepato Ternano"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('16ab4530-d565-7e43-e9c0-64575eddfdc5', 'IT', 'Italy', 'sweets_pastry_confectionery', 'Panforte di Siena IGP', '["Panforte di Siena IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Tuscan Christmas dense fruit-and-nut cake from Siena (medieval origin), packed with candied citrus peel, almonds, hazelnuts, honey, sugar, spices (cinnamon, clove, nutmeg, pepper, coriander). Two main types — Margherita (white-sugar topped) and Nero (darker, more spiced). Dense chewy texture, intensely sweet-spiced complex flavor.', 'Christmas dessert in Tuscan restaurants, sliced thinly with Vin Santo, on cheese boards (especially with Pecorino), in gift hampers.', '["whole-cake-100g-gift-box", "whole-cake-250g-gift-box", "whole-cake-500g-gift-box", "whole-cake-1kg-gift-box", "sliced-vacuum-150g"]'::jsonb, '[10, 11, 12]'::jsonb, '["Panforte Senese", "Sienese panforte", "Panforte Margherita", "Panforte Nero"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('96edf0c2-3345-947b-26d2-ad2dded42b4a', 'IT', 'Italy', 'sweets_pastry_confectionery', 'Ricciarelli di Siena IGP', '["Ricciarelli di Siena IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Tuscan almond paste cookies from Siena, traditional medieval origin. Distinctive lozenge shape, soft chewy almond-paste interior dusted with powdered sugar, intensely flavored with sweet almond, vanilla, citrus zest.', 'Sienese-Tuscan dessert service, paired with Vin Santo and dessert wines, in gift packaging, alongside cantuccini for ambient sweets retail.', '["retail-bag-150g", "retail-bag-300g", "gift-pack-tin-200g", "foodservice-bulk-2kg"]'::jsonb, '[10, 11, 12]'::jsonb, '["Ricciarelli", "Ricciarelli senesi", "Sienese almond cookies"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('1dbe4631-e5db-c2b0-d952-bb9663b21318', 'IT', 'Italy', 'sweets_pastry_confectionery', 'Torrone di Bagnara IGP', '["Torrone di Bagnara IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Calabrian nougat from Bagnara Calabra area (Reggio Calabria province), traditional honey-and-egg-white nougat with almonds and hazelnuts, sometimes coated in dark chocolate. Crisp-chewy texture, intense honey-nut flavor, characteristic spicing (cinnamon, cloves) in some sub-styles.', 'Calabrian dessert service, paired with sweet wines and digestifs, gift packaging, on dessert platters with regional dolci.', '["whole-bar-100g", "whole-bar-200g-gift-box", "whole-bar-300g-gift-box", "sliced-vacuum-150g"]'::jsonb, '[11, 12]'::jsonb, '["Torrone Bagnara", "Bagnara nougat"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('4152ee50-83df-7509-f410-1aa31b50e8c2', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Bergamotto di Reggio Calabria – Olio essenziale DOP', '["Bergamotto di Reggio Calabria – Olio essenziale DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Already described in fruits_nuts section under "Bergamotto di Reggio Calabria DOP (essential oil)" — not duplicated here. Reference: vivid yellow oil with intensely aromatic floral-citrus profile, foundational note in Earl Grey tea and Eau de Cologne.', 'See fruits_nuts section.', '["glass-bottle-30ml", "glass-bottle-50ml", "glass-bottle-100ml", "glass-bottle-250ml", "professional-bulk-1L"]'::jsonb, '[11, 12, 1, 2]'::jsonb, '["Bergamotto Reggio Calabria", "Reggio bergamot oil"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('406b9f59-7354-449f-4a20-0fd3731e71f9', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Cappero di Pantelleria IGP', '["Cappero di Pantelleria IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Sicilian capers from Pantelleria volcanic island, traditional salt-cured (not vinegar-pickled). Small to medium dark-green buds, intensely aromatic with characteristic salty-pungent flavor and complex fruity-floral notes from volcanic soil and sea spray.', 'Pasta puttanesca and Sicilian-style pasta; tartare and crudo seasoning; chicken alla Romana and vitello tonnato; pizza Napoletana topping; tuna tartare; fish carpaccio.', '["salt-cured-jar-100g", "salt-cured-jar-200g", "salt-cured-jar-500g", "vinegar-pickled-jar-200g", "gift-pack-100g", "bulk-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Cappero pantesco", "Pantelleria caper"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('d2205c87-0c79-c3ab-d6f0-baf66b763fcf', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Fagioli Bianchi di Rotonda DOP', '["Fagioli Bianchi di Rotonda DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Lucanian large white bean from Rotonda area (Pollino park). Distinctive large size, very thin skin, creamy floury texture when cooked, mild sweet flavor.', 'In Lucanian rustic dishes, fagioli con cotenne, paired with peperoni cruschi, in soups.', '["dried-vacuum-pack-500g", "dried-vacuum-pack-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Fagiolo bianco di Rotonda", "Rotonda white bean"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('bfced626-e53f-c14f-eb5a-9548750a9981', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Fagiolo di Cuneo IGP', '["Fagiolo di Cuneo IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Already described above (combined entry ''Fagiolo Cuneo''). For Iriska data records, treat as same entry.', 'Same as Fagiolo Cuneo above.', '["dried-vacuum-pack-500g", "dried-vacuum-pack-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Fagiolo cuneese"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('1dc99e29-7fcd-b880-0ba9-357b57b019d8', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Fungo di Borgotaro IGP', '["Fungo di Borgotaro IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Emilian-Tuscan porcino mushroom from Borgotaro area (Parma-Massa-Carrara provinces). Premium Boletus edulis, large meaty cap with intense earthy-mushroomy flavor, dense firm texture, characteristic chestnut-forest aroma.', 'Tagliatelle ai funghi porcini, risotto, raw thinly-sliced with parmigiano, grilled cap, in autumn pasta dishes, dried for stock and reconstitution.', '["fresh-bulk-1kg", "fresh-bulk-2kg", "dried-vacuum-pack-50g", "dried-vacuum-pack-100g", "dried-vacuum-pack-500g", "frozen-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[8, 9, 10, 11]'::jsonb, '["Porcino di Borgotaro", "Borgotaro porcini"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('1663b0ca-d5b9-f9ce-d678-353c568ab029', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Patata del Fucino IGP', '["Patata del Fucino IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Abruzzese potato from Fucino plain (former lake bed, mineral-rich soil). Yellow flesh, balanced starch, well-suited to multiple preparations.', 'Gnocchi production, mashed (purè), roasted, in regional Abruzzese stews and minestrone.', '["mesh-bag-2kg", "mesh-bag-5kg", "crate-10kg", "crate-25kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Patata fucense", "Fucino potato"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('ebd1fc60-a4ab-7075-c666-f8360841b42d', 'IT', 'Italy', 'preserves_pantry', 'Cipollotto Nocerino DOP', '["Cipollotto Nocerino DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Campanian young spring onion from Nocera area (Salerno province). Slender white bulb with green stem, mildly sweet flavor, crisp tender texture.', 'Fresh in salads, antipasto, grilled with EVOO, on focaccia.', '["bunch-fresh-300g", "bunch-fresh-500g", "crate-fresh-5kg"]'::jsonb, '[3, 4, 5, 6]'::jsonb, '["Nocera spring onion", "Cipollotto nocerino"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('943475d3-a211-a156-050a-f87d22db3c53', 'IT', 'Italy', 'rice_pasta_grains', 'Pagnotta del Dittaino DOP', '["Pagnotta del Dittaino DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Sicilian rustic round bread from Dittaino valley (Enna province), 100% durum wheat semolina (Italian wheat varieties Simeto, Duilio, Iride, Ciccio etc.). Golden-brown thick crust, dense yellow crumb, full wheat flavor with characteristic semolina aroma, long-keeping (3-4 days fresh).', 'Bread service for Sicilian cuisine, especially with caponata and Sicilian salumi; sliced for bruschetta; toasted with EVOO and tomato; in pane cunzato.', '["whole-loaf-500g", "whole-loaf-1kg", "half-loaf-vacuum-500g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Pagnotta Dittaino", "Sicilian semolina bread"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('6ff472c2-cc2a-f195-3d03-e13a5fd0fe23', 'IT', 'Italy', 'rice_pasta_grains', 'Pane casareccio di Genzano IGP', '["Pane casareccio di Genzano IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Lazio rustic round bread from Genzano (Castelli Romani area), traditional wood-oven baking, dusted with bran. Thick dark-brown crust, dense moist crumb, full wheat flavor with characteristic wood-oven aroma — long-keeping rustic bread.', 'Roman bread service, especially with porchetta di Ariccia (Genzano is in same area), bruschetta, panini, classic with Roman trattoria meals.', '["whole-loaf-1kg", "whole-loaf-2kg", "half-loaf-vacuum-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Pane Genzano", "Genzano bread"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('7ecc3382-8282-831b-1814-6598c094ad32', 'IT', 'Italy', 'rice_pasta_grains', 'Bra DOP — pasta filata cheese (no, this is Cheese — already in 3.2; cross-reference noted)', '["Bra DOP — pasta filata cheese (no, this is Cheese — already in 3.2; cross-reference noted)"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, '', '', '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, TRUE, 'L2'),
