  ('6c2b142c-3842-30b8-2d19-cf3c79eccbbb', 'ES', 'Spain', 'olive_oils_olives', 'Aceite de Baena DOP', '["Aceite de Baena DOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Andalusian EVOO from Córdoba province (Baena area), Picudo and Hojiblanca cultivars predominant. Medium-intense fruity with characteristic notes of artichoke, fresh almond, green tomato, balanced bitter-pungent finish — Spain''s first olive oil DOP (1986), benchmark of Andalusian quality.', 'Premium Spanish EVOO — drizzled on gazpacho andaluz, salmorejo, on grilled fish (lubina, dorada), in escabeches, and on tostadas con tomate; foundational ingredient in alta cocina andaluza.', '["glass-bottle-250ml", "glass-bottle-500ml", "glass-bottle-750ml", "tin-3L", "tin-5L", "PET-canister-3L", "professional-bulk-25L"]'::jsonb, '[11, 12, 1, 2]'::jsonb, '["Baena DOP", "Aceite de Baena", "Picudo de Baena"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
