  ('c85b817b-f286-3d69-14c0-9bd29979c531', 'FR', 'France', 'cured_meats_charcuterie', 'Saucisse de Toulouse IGP (status — verify Layer 1; major French sausage but verify exact GI status)', '["Saucisse de Toulouse IGP (status — verify Layer 1; major French sausage but verify exact GI status)"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'South-west fresh pork sausage with garlic, salt, pepper, no smoking. Long coiled link in natural casing, coarse-ground rosy pork, robust savory flavor with garlic and pepper notes, soft fresh texture.', 'Foundation of cassoulet de Castelnaudary; grilled or pan-fried with lentilles vertes du Puy; in choucroute alsacienne (variant); classic French bistro service.', '["coiled-link-vacuum-300-500g", "individual-link-150g", "pre-cooked-vacuum-300g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Saucisse de Toulouse", "Toulouse sausage"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('5db3eba0-8648-020b-8970-5ec6fef91b26', 'FR', 'France', 'cured_meats_charcuterie', 'Tripoux d''Auvergne IGP (cured-meat-adjacent dish, verify Layer 1)', '["Tripoux d''Auvergne IGP (cured-meat-adjacent dish, verify Layer 1)"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Auvergne cooked dish — small parcels of sheep tripe stuffed with sausage meat, slow-simmered.', 'Auvergne breakfast/regional dish; restaurant heritage menu.', '["vacuum-pack-cooked-500g", "jar-cooked-700g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Tripoux"]'::jsonb, TRUE, 'L2'),
  ('681d7e5f-44c2-c8fc-72df-ab889d94106d', 'FR', 'France', 'cured_meats_charcuterie', 'Boudin noir de Mortagne (regional, status verify)', '["Boudin noir de Mortagne (regional, status verify)"]'::jsonb, 'OTHER', '["OTHER"]'::jsonb, 'Norman black blood-pudding sausage from Mortagne-au-Perche. Dark mahogany color, soft fine texture, rich blood-and-spice flavor.', 'Pan-fried with apples (Norman classic); on Norman charcuterie boards; pairs with cidre.', '["vacuum-pack-400g", "individual-link-200g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Boudin noir de Mortagne"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('c0954f30-e605-6505-20c1-999a31cbdf6f', 'FR', 'France', 'cured_meats_charcuterie', 'Saucisson sec lyonnais (status verify)', '["Saucisson sec lyonnais (status verify)"]'::jsonb, 'OTHER', '["OTHER"]'::jsonb, 'Lyonnais dry-cured pork salami, the iconic Lyon bouchon charcuterie.', 'Plateau de charcuterie in Lyonnais bouchons; with cervelle de canut (cheese); pairs with Beaujolais.', '["whole-piece-vacuum-300-500g", "deli-sliced-vacuum-100g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Saucisson sec de Lyon", "Rosette de Lyon"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('84b63305-d5d2-e8bf-d314-4499af304ffd', 'FR', 'France', 'olive_oils_olives', 'Huile d''olive de Provence AOP', '["Huile d''olive de Provence AOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Provençal regional EVOO AOP, blend of Provençal cultivars (Aglandau, Salonenque, Picholine, Bouteillan). Light-medium fruity intensity, balanced harmonious flavor with characteristic Provençal notes of artichoke, fresh almond, green herbs, light bitter-pungent finish.', 'Foundation Provençal EVOO — drizzled on tapenade, ratatouille, tomates Provençales, grilled fish, salade niçoise; raw on fougasse and pistou.', '["glass-bottle-250ml", "glass-bottle-500ml", "glass-bottle-750ml", "tin-3L", "tin-5L", "PET-canister-3L"]'::jsonb, '[11, 12, 1, 2]'::jsonb, '["Huile d''olive de Provence", "Provence AOP olive oil"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('ae6d32d7-6792-faea-54b3-309d91fc80c7', 'FR', 'France', 'olive_oils_olives', 'Huile d''olive de Nîmes AOP', '["Huile d''olive de Nîmes AOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Languedoc-Gard EVOO from Nîmes area, Picholine cultivar predominant. Medium fruity intensity, balanced bitter-pungent profile, characteristic notes of fresh almond, artichoke, green herbs.', 'Languedoc cuisine, Mediterranean fish preparations, drizzled on roasted vegetables.', '["glass-bottle-500ml", "glass-bottle-750ml", "tin-3L"]'::jsonb, '[11, 12, 1, 2]'::jsonb, '["Huile d''olive de Nîmes"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('0aab5f52-995d-b9c8-2763-768cdd326c62', 'FR', 'France', 'olive_oils_olives', 'Huile d''olive de la Vallée des Baux-de-Provence AOP', '["Huile d''olive de la Vallée des Baux-de-Provence AOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Provençal EVOO from Vallée des Baux (Bouches-du-Rhône), distinctive olive selections including the rare "olive maturée" (slightly fermented black olive paste-like style). Two styles: standard fruité vert (green-fruity) and unique fruité noir (black-fruity, fermented with characteristic tapenade-cocoa-mushroom notes — a distinctive AOP feature).', 'Premium Provençal finishing oil; black-fruity style drizzled on roasted lamb and game; green-fruity on fresh tomatoes, ratatouille, tapenade.', '["glass-bottle-250ml", "glass-bottle-500ml", "glass-bottle-750ml", "tin-3L"]'::jsonb, '[11, 12, 1, 2]'::jsonb, '["Vallée des Baux-de-Provence", "Baux-de-Provence olive oil", "Fruité Noir des Baux (premium sub-style)"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('805c6faa-0625-8caa-27ee-6b820d197f70', 'FR', 'France', 'olive_oils_olives', 'Huile d''olive de Nyons AOP', '["Huile d''olive de Nyons AOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Drômois EVOO from Nyons area, Tanche cultivar (rare and distinctive). Light-medium fruity intensity, very gentle balanced flavor, distinctive sweet-mild profile with delicate butter and almond notes — among France''s most distinctive olive oils.', 'Premium finishing oil for Provençal cuisine; on raw vegetables and crudités; with tapenade and aïoli; Drôme regional centerpiece.', '["glass-bottle-250ml", "glass-bottle-500ml", "glass-bottle-750ml", "tin-3L"]'::jsonb, '[11, 12, 1, 2]'::jsonb, '["Huile d''olive de Nyons", "Nyons AOP", "Tanche oil"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('6ec7cf7e-3217-a50d-1d23-59a72dffc5d1', 'FR', 'France', 'olive_oils_olives', 'Olives noires de Nyons AOP', '["Olives noires de Nyons AOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Drômois black table olive (Tanche cultivar, same as oil AOP) cured by traditional brine or salt method. Distinctive wrinkled dark-purple to black appearance, very tender flesh, sweet-savory mild flavor with characteristic gentle profile (less intense than Greek-style olives).', 'Tapenade noire (signature Provençal preparation), mixed olive selections, on cheese boards, in Provençal salads, with raw vegetables (apéritif).', '["jar-glass-200g-brine", "jar-glass-500g-brine", "vacuum-pack-200g", "jar-tapenade-180g", "bucket-2kg-brine"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Olives de Nyons", "Tanche olives"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('d567c62f-1342-b68c-dd50-3f653c6c2c00', 'FR', 'France', 'olive_oils_olives', 'Huile d''olive d''Aix-en-Provence AOP', '["Huile d''olive d''Aix-en-Provence AOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Provençal EVOO from Aix-en-Provence area, blend of Aglandau, Cayanne, Picholine, Salonenque. Medium fruity intensity, balanced bitter-pungent, characteristic Provençal notes of artichoke, almond, fresh herbs.', 'Provençal cuisine, drizzled on bouillabaisse, ratatouille, salade niçoise.', '["glass-bottle-500ml", "glass-bottle-750ml", "tin-3L", "tin-5L"]'::jsonb, '[11, 12, 1, 2]'::jsonb, '["Aix-en-Provence olive oil"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('b04b8b37-f007-4458-1c3e-eb18e4eb572a', 'FR', 'France', 'olive_oils_olives', 'Huile d''olive de Haute-Provence AOP', '["Huile d''olive de Haute-Provence AOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Haute-Provence EVOO from Alpes-de-Haute-Provence-Vaucluse, Aglandau cultivar predominant. Medium-intense fruity, robust bitter-pungent profile, characteristic notes of artichoke, fresh almond, alpine-Provençal herbs.', 'Premium Provençal finishing oil; drizzled on grilled lamb and Sisteron-area meats; with Provençal pulses; raw on tapenade.', '["glass-bottle-250ml", "glass-bottle-500ml", "glass-bottle-750ml", "tin-3L"]'::jsonb, '[11, 12, 1, 2]'::jsonb, '["Huile d''olive de Haute-Provence", "Aglandau de Haute-Provence"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('33fd9432-3ee2-c9ff-805f-40e91105e740', 'FR', 'France', 'olive_oils_olives', 'Huile d''olive de Nice AOP', '["Huile d''olive de Nice AOP", "Olives de Nice AOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO", "PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Niçois EVOO from Alpes-Maritimes coast, Cailletier cultivar (also known as Niçoise olive — the small black salade-niçoise olive). Light fruity intensity, very delicate balanced flavor, sweet-mild profile with light almond notes — among France''s gentlest oils. Olives: small black-purple Cailletier, brined whole, intensely flavored despite small size.', '**Foundation of Niçois cuisine** — salade niçoise (oil and olives both essential), socca (chickpea pancake), pissaladière, ratatouille; pairs with Bellet wines.', '["Oil: glass-bottle-250ml", "glass-bottle-500ml", "glass-bottle-750ml. Olives: jar-200g", "jar-500g", "vacuum-pack-200g", "bucket-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[11, 12, 1, 2]'::jsonb, '["Huile d''olive de Nice", "Olives de Nice", "Cailletier olive", "Niçoise olive"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('98ce6ab0-aae7-5902-ede5-f87a12c7b898', 'FR', 'France', 'olive_oils_olives', 'Huile d''olive de Corse AOP', '["Huile d''olive de Corse AOP", "Oliu di Corsica AOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO", "PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Corsican EVOO from heritage cultivars (Sabina, Capannace, Curtinese, Zinzala, Ghjermana). Light-medium fruity intensity, very delicate balanced flavor, distinctively soft sweet profile with light almond and fresh-herb notes — Mediterranean island terroir.', 'Foundation Corsican cuisine — drizzled on grilled fish, pulpu (octopus), Corsican charcuterie, fiadone (cheese cake); pairs with Patrimonio and Vermentino di Corsica wines.', '["glass-bottle-250ml", "glass-bottle-500ml", "glass-bottle-750ml", "tin-3L"]'::jsonb, '[11, 12, 1, 2]'::jsonb, '["Oliu di Corsica", "Huile d''olive de Corse", "Corsican olive oil"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('072f036a-1b5f-f98b-6027-7abefd0c3313', 'FR', 'France', 'olive_oils_olives', 'Lucques du Languedoc AOP', '["Lucques du Languedoc AOP", "Olive Lucques AOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO", "PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Languedoc green table olive (Lucques cultivar) from Hérault. Distinctive elongated curved-crescent shape (the "green crescent moon"), bright green color, firm crisp flesh, mild buttery-sweet flavor with characteristic delicate herbal notes — the Languedoc apéritif olive par excellence.', 'Premium apéritif olive — served chilled with rosé wine; on antipasto boards; in olive selections; cocktail garnish; in salade languedocienne.', '["jar-200g-brine", "jar-500g-brine", "vacuum-pack-200g", "bucket-1kg-brine", "gift-pack-200g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Lucques", "Lucques du Languedoc", "Olive de Languedoc", "Languedoc Lucques olive"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('b261d2dc-5eb3-b1ab-99b9-d15319594c01', 'FR', 'France', 'fruits_nuts', 'Noix de Grenoble AOP', '["Noix de Grenoble AOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Dauphiné walnut from Grenoble area (Isère-Drôme-Savoie), three traditional varieties (Franquette, Mayette, Parisienne). Premium walnut with golden-tan shell and pale-cream sweet kernel, balanced rich nutty flavor with characteristic delicate notes (less bitter than other walnuts) — the iconic French walnut, AOP since 1938 (first French nut AOP).', '**Plateau de fromages staple** — paired with Roquefort and Bleu d''Auvergne; in salade aux noix with Comté or Beaufort; in walnut bread, walnut tart, walnut oil production; pastry use; chopped on aged cheeses.', '["in-shell-mesh-bag-1kg", "in-shell-mesh-bag-3kg", "shelled-vacuum-pack-200g", "shelled-vacuum-pack-500g", "shelled-vacuum-pack-1kg", "gift-pack-shelled-300g", "walnut-oil-bottle-250ml"]'::jsonb, '[10, 11, 12, 1]'::jsonb, '["Noix de Grenoble", "Grenoble walnut"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('2ef25ca0-494b-268e-8005-3d7eaa5940d2', 'FR', 'France', 'fruits_nuts', 'Noix du Périgord AOP', '["Noix du Périgord AOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Périgord walnut AOP from Dordogne, three varieties (Marbot, Corne, Grandjean, Franquette). Sweet rich nutty flavor, characteristic Périgord-truffle-walnut terroir association.', 'Plateau de fromages with Périgord cheeses; **classic Périgord walnut oil** for salade aux noix; in walnut cake (gâteau aux noix de Périgord); paired with Cabécou and Rocamadour cheeses.', '["in-shell-mesh-bag-1kg", "shelled-vacuum-pack-200g", "walnut-oil-bottle-250ml"]'::jsonb, '[10, 11, 12, 1]'::jsonb, '["Noix du Périgord", "Périgord walnut"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('f07d2c78-e14f-2e8e-e074-d03efdd4c5c2', 'FR', 'France', 'fruits_nuts', 'Châtaigne d''Ardèche AOP', '["Châtaigne d''Ardèche AOP", "Marron d''Ardèche AOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO", "PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Ardèche chestnut AOP, multiple traditional varieties (Bouche Rouge, Comballe, Pourette, Sardonne, Aguyane, Garinche, Merle, Précoce des Vans). Sweet creamy starchy flesh, characteristic Cevenol-mountain flavor.', 'Caldarroste (roasted chestnuts), candied (marrons glacés — Ardèche is major production center), Ardèche chestnut soup and ravioli, dried for chestnut flour (used in traditional Ardèche bread), in autumn cheese boards with Pélardon.', '["crate-fresh-10kg", "crate-fresh-15kg", "vacuum-pack-cooked-500g", "frozen-peeled-1kg", "dried-1kg", "marron-glacé-gift-300g", "chestnut-flour-500g", "chestnut-cream-jar-250g"]'::jsonb, '[10, 11, 12]'::jsonb, '["Châtaigne d''Ardèche", "Marron d''Ardèche", "Cevenol chestnut"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('b68dc012-3ab8-5181-9606-70e013b46f6f', 'FR', 'France', 'fruits_nuts', 'Châtaigne de Corse AOP', '["Châtaigne de Corse AOP", "Castagna di Corsica AOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO", "PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Corsican chestnut AOP from Castagniccia region, traditional sweet chestnut. Characteristic Corsican-terroir flavor; foundation of traditional Corsican mountain agriculture.', 'Corsican chestnut flour (pulenta corsa, traditional polenta-style dish; Corsican chestnut beer Pietra), dessert preparations (fiadone variants); roasted whole.', '["crate-fresh-10kg", "vacuum-pack-cooked-500g", "dried-1kg", "chestnut-flour-1kg", "gift-pack-300g"]'::jsonb, '[10, 11, 12]'::jsonb, '["Castagna di Corsica", "Châtaigne de Corse", "Corsican chestnut"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('c0207473-fd8f-0eb5-eeeb-d93b8cadec30', 'FR', 'France', 'fruits_nuts', 'Pruneau d''Agen IGP', '["Pruneau d''Agen IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Lot-et-Garonne dried prune (Prune d''Ente variety) from Agen area, IGP since 2002. Dark mahogany color, soft chewy texture, intensely sweet flavor with characteristic plum-honey notes and complex caramel-fruit profile — France''s most famous dried fruit.', 'Lapin aux pruneaux (rabbit with prunes — south-west classic), in prune-Armagnac compote, far breton (with cream), petit-four mignardise; stuffed pruneaux fourrés (Agen specialty).', '["vacuum-pack-200g", "vacuum-pack-500g", "vacuum-pack-1kg", "gift-pack-300g", "professional-bulk-5kg", "pruneau-Armagnac-jar-300g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Pruneau d''Agen", "Prune d''Ente", "Agen prune"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
