  ('b3b7dee5-2a7b-3739-6956-52e859466022', 'FR', 'France', 'vinegars_condiments', 'Vinaigre de Reims (status verify Layer 1)', '["Vinaigre de Reims (status verify Layer 1)"]'::jsonb, 'OTHER', '["OTHER"]'::jsonb, 'Champagne wine vinegar.', 'Champenois cuisine; in vinaigrettes; deglazing.', '["glass-bottle-500ml"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Vinaigre de Reims"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('7e43f405-231b-f755-b0ef-8dd719d278d5', 'FR', 'France', 'spices_salt_herbs', 'Piment d''Espelette AOP', '["Piment d''Espelette AOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Basque chili pepper AOP from Espelette area, sun-and-air-dried then ground. Distinctive bright-red ground powder, balanced moderate heat (around 4,000 SHU — gentler than cayenne), characteristic sweet-fruity-smoky flavor with red-pepper-paprika notes — the iconic French Basque spice.', '**Foundation of Basque cuisine** — in piperade, axoa, in marinades, sprinkled on meats and seafood; replacement for paprika and cayenne in fine dining; pairs with Irouléguy and Jurançon wines.', '["glass-jar-40g", "glass-jar-100g", "glass-jar-200g", "professional-bulk-1kg", "fresh-string-traditional-100g", "gift-pack-100g", "paste-jar-100g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Piment d''Espelette", "Espelette pepper", "Ezpeletako biperra (Basque)"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('95975ab4-46c8-7adf-6214-213bab990c98', 'FR', 'France', 'spices_salt_herbs', 'Sel de Guérande IGP', '["Sel de Guérande IGP", "Fleur de sel de Guérande IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI", "PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Brittany sea salt IGP from Guérande salt-marshes (Loire-Atlantique), traditional hand-harvested. **Sel gris de Guérande** (grey coarse): mineral-rich grey crystals, savory-mineral flavor, ideal for cooking and seasoning. **Fleur de sel de Guérande** (white-flake): premium top-skimmed delicate flakes, light salty flavor with subtle sweet-mineral notes, finishing salt.', '**Sel gris** for general kitchen use, brining, blanching, pasta water; **Fleur de sel** as premium finishing salt — sprinkled on grilled fish, foie gras, fresh tomatoes, chocolate desserts (the canonical fleur-de-sel-on-caramel pairing).', '["Sel gris: paper-bag-500g", "paper-bag-1kg", "professional-bulk-5kg", "professional-bulk-25kg. Fleur de sel: glass-jar-100g", "glass-jar-200g", "gift-pack-100g", "professional-bulk-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Sel de Guérande", "Fleur de sel de Guérande", "Guérande sea salt", "Brittany sea salt"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('025f2719-a415-37e0-3e81-36d2b44e359e', 'FR', 'France', 'spices_salt_herbs', 'Sel de l''Île de Ré (status — possibly under Sel de Guérande or separate IGP)', '["Sel de l''Île de Ré (status — possibly under Sel de Guérande or separate IGP)"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Île de Ré salt from Charente-Maritime sea-marsh harvesting.', 'Same as Guérande sel gris and fleur de sel applications.', '["Same as Guérande"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Sel de l''Île de Ré"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('7421ae90-7baa-203d-e2dd-47679bc93e7e', 'FR', 'France', 'spices_salt_herbs', 'Lavande de Provence (status — Huile essentielle de Lavande de Haute-Provence AOP if cosmetic-side; verify)', '["Lavande de Provence (status — Huile essentielle de Lavande de Haute-Provence AOP if cosmetic-side; verify)"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, '[DATA THIN — primarily cosmetic/perfume side] Provençal lavender for culinary use.', 'Pâtisserie use (lavender macaron, lavender-honey crème brûlée), with herbes de Provence.', '["glass-jar-50g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Lavande de Provence"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('aea91c3b-9d80-4a88-8c67-96d331115b34', 'FR', 'France', 'spices_salt_herbs', 'Herbes de Provence (status — Herbes de Provence Label Rouge, not strictly IGP, verify Layer 1 inclusion)', '["Herbes de Provence (status — Herbes de Provence Label Rouge, not strictly IGP, verify Layer 1 inclusion)"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Provençal dried-herb mixture (thyme, rosemary, savory, oregano, basil, marjoram). Aromatic with characteristic Mediterranean profile.', 'Foundation Provençal seasoning; on grilled meats, vegetables, ratatouille.', '["paper-bag-50g", "paper-bag-100g", "glass-jar-50g", "professional-bulk-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Herbes de Provence"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('45452e70-3524-e0e8-f267-171992d52189', 'FR', 'France', 'spices_salt_herbs', 'Genièvre de Houlle (juniper-related, status verify)', '["Genièvre de Houlle (juniper-related, status verify)"]'::jsonb, 'OTHER', '["OTHER"]'::jsonb, 'Northern France juniper distillate.', 'As gin-style spirit for Northern French preparations.', '["glass-bottle-700ml"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Genièvre"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('b89837ba-ab78-6b2e-6db2-6ce964882524', 'FR', 'France', 'honey_sweeteners', 'Miel de Provence IGP', '["Miel de Provence IGP"]'::jsonb, 'PGI', '["PGI"]'::jsonb, 'Provençal honey IGP, multiple varieties (lavender, rosemary, thyme, all-flower / "toutes fleurs"). **Miel de lavande** is the iconic style: pale gold to amber, intensely floral-aromatic with characteristic lavender-perfumed notes, balanced sweet-floral flavor. **Miel de romarin**: very pale, delicate floral. **Miel toutes fleurs**: amber, complex multi-flower profile.', '**Premium pastry honey** (especially Lavande for macarons, panna cotta, lavender ice cream); on Provençal cheese boards (paired with Banon, Pélardon); drizzled on goat cheese; in marinades.', '["glass-jar-250g", "glass-jar-500g", "glass-jar-1kg", "gift-pack-Lavande-250g", "professional-bulk-5kg"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Miel de Provence", "Miel de Lavande de Provence", "Provence honey"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('efe8c764-6a89-323d-e466-875007cbb961', 'FR', 'France', 'honey_sweeteners', 'Miel de Sapin des Vosges AOP', '["Miel de Sapin des Vosges AOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Vosges fir-tree honeydew AOP — the iconic French "miel de sapin". Dark amber to mahogany color, very thick consistency, intensely aromatic with characteristic resin-pine-balsamic flavor, robust complex profile distinctly different from floral honeys.', '**Plateau de fromages** (premium pairing with Munster, aged Comté, Gruyère); in tea and tisanes; pastry use for distinctive flavor; pairs with Vin Jaune and Champagne.', '["glass-jar-250g", "glass-jar-500g", "gift-pack-250g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Miel de Sapin des Vosges", "Vosges fir honey"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('b79241bf-df06-0455-64ef-29b703bd1f00', 'FR', 'France', 'honey_sweeteners', 'Miel de Corse AOP', '["Miel de Corse AOP", "Mele di Corsica AOP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO", "PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Corsican honey AOP, six varieties tied to seasonal pasture: Printemps (spring all-flower), Maquis de printemps (spring maquis-shrub), Miellats du maquis (maquis honeydew), Châtaigneraie (chestnut), Maquis d''été (summer maquis), Maquis d''automne (autumn maquis with arbutus). Each style has distinct flavor — chestnut version intense bitter-tannic, maquis versions complex herbal-floral with characteristic Corsican-flora notes (myrtle, rosemary, lavender-de-mer).', '**Foundation of Corsican gastronomy** — paired with Brocciu Passu cheese; in fiadone; on Corsican charcuterie boards; with chestnut-flour preparations.', '["glass-jar-250g", "glass-jar-500g", "gift-pack-by-variety-250g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Mele di Corsica", "Miel de Corse"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
