  ('66f312e9-23f2-91b3-6332-d11534feb7a4', 'GR', 'Greece', 'cheeses_dairy', 'Feta POP', '["Feta POP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Greek brine-cured sheep''s milk cheese POP (with optional goat milk up to 30%), the iconic Greek cheese — globally protected as Greek-only since 2002 EU ruling. Aged minimum 2 months in brine. Bright white color, crumbly-yet-creamy texture, intensely salty-tangy flavor with characteristic sheep-milk complexity. Greece''s most-consumed cheese (per-capita highest in EU) and major export.', '**Foundation of Greek cuisine** — essential in horiatiki salata (Greek salad), spanakopita (spinach pie), saganaki (pan-fried), tyropita (cheese pie), in mezze boards, on grilled vegetables; **the iconic Greek table cheese** worldwide.', '["vacuum-pack-block-200g", "vacuum-pack-block-400g", "vacuum-pack-block-1kg", "brine-tin-1kg", "brine-tin-3kg", "brine-tin-5kg", "brine-bucket-10kg", "crumbled-pre-pack-200g", "gift-pack-200g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Feta", "Φέτα", "Greek feta"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('70f2e7db-4039-c42a-2ef6-b51d3138857e', 'GR', 'Greece', 'cheeses_dairy', 'Graviera Naxou POP', '["Graviera Naxou POP", "Graviera Kritis POP", "Graviera Agrafon POP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO", "PDO", "PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Greek hard cow''s-or-mixed-milk cheese POPs (gruyere-family, named "Graviera" from "Gruyère"). Aged 3+ months. Pale ivory paste, firm dense texture with small eyes, balanced sweet-nutty-savory flavor — Greek hard cheese tradition. **Graviera Naxou** (Cyclades island, mostly cow milk) is among the most renowned; **Graviera Kritis** (Crete, sheep-and-goat milk) has more pronounced flavor; **Graviera Agrafon** (mainland mountain) is artisanal.', 'Greek tyrokomeio (cheese course); **saganaki** (pan-fried); **bougatsa** (cheese pie variations); grated on pasta and gratins; with melon and ham.', '["wheel-full-7-15kg", "wheel-quarter-vacuum-2-4kg", "wedge-vacuum-300g", "wedge-vacuum-150g", "grated-pre-pack-100g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Graviera Naxou", "Graviera Kritis", "Graviera Agrafon", "Greek gruyere"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('8354c7ea-6402-1a00-eafd-09198e6c33c9', 'GR', 'Greece', 'cheeses_dairy', 'Kasseri POP', '["Kasseri POP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Greek hard sheep-and-goat-milk cheese POP from Macedonia and Thessaly. Aged 3+ months, pasta-filata-style stretched-curd preparation. Pale ivory paste, firm chewy texture (like a firmer mozzarella), mild buttery flavor.', '**Saganaki** (pan-fried until golden, doused in lemon and brandy — flambé service is popular in tourist tavernas); melted in tyropita and Greek-style sandwiches.', '["wheel-full-3-9kg", "wedge-vacuum-300g", "wedge-vacuum-150g", "slabs-vacuum-300g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Kasseri", "Κασέρι"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('2f1706c4-f0f1-d626-aa9c-f735ee2e599c', 'GR', 'Greece', 'cheeses_dairy', 'Kefalograviera POP', '["Kefalograviera POP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Greek hard sheep-and-goat-milk cheese POP, aged 3+ months. Combines characteristics of Kefalotyri (very salty, hard) and Graviera (sweet-nutty). Pale ivory paste, firm dense texture, intensely savory salty-tangy-nutty flavor.', '**Saganaki** premium choice; grated for pasta dishes; in mezze boards; in baked pasta dishes (pasticio).', '["wheel-full-7-15kg", "wedge-vacuum-300g", "grated-pre-pack-100g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Kefalograviera"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('0e9e1529-4675-a87a-0428-569332441132', 'GR', 'Greece', 'cheeses_dairy', 'Kefalotyri (status — heritage; Kefalotyri itself is generic, but Kefalograviera POP and other regional Kefalotyri POPs may exist; verify Layer 1)', '["Kefalotyri (status — heritage; Kefalotyri itself is generic, but Kefalograviera POP and other regional Kefalotyri POPs may exist; verify Layer 1)"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Generic Greek hard salted sheep-and-goat-milk cheese, very firm grating texture.', 'Grated on pastitsio, moussaka.', '["wedge-vacuum-300g", "grated-pre-pack-100g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Kefalotyri"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('6d233410-6e62-09bc-e2c4-e4c19d320069', 'GR', 'Greece', 'cheeses_dairy', 'Manouri POP', '["Manouri POP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Greek fresh whey-cheese POP (sheep-and-goat-milk whey from feta production, similar to Italian ricotta but firmer). Bright white, soft tender texture, sweet creamy flavor with mild salty-tangy edge.', 'Greek cheese plate (sweet); with honey and walnuts; in sweet-and-savoury mezze; in sponguze (Greek pastry); with figs and grapes.', '["vacuum-pack-cylinder-300-500g", "vacuum-pack-cylinder-1kg"]'::jsonb, '[3, 4, 5, 6, 7]'::jsonb, '["Manouri", "Manoyri"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('cd45716a-06f5-c07f-1f7f-7d65c9c8cf5b', 'GR', 'Greece', 'cheeses_dairy', 'Anthotyros', '["Anthotyros", "Anthotyros Frescos", "Anthotyros Xeros (status — heritage; if separately POP-registered)"]'::jsonb, 'OTHER', '["OTHER", "OTHER", "PDO"]'::jsonb, '[DATA THIN if not POP] Greek whey-cheese, fresh (Frescos) or aged (Xeros) styles.', 'Cheese plates, mezze.', '["vacuum-pack-300-500g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Anthotyros", "Mizithra (related)"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
