  ('0c9ddc73-ed18-8eff-9860-7f71824bdaca', 'GR', 'Greece', 'fruits_nuts', 'Korinthiaki Stafida POP', '["Korinthiaki Stafida POP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Peloponnesian dried-currant POP from Corinthian (Korinth) cultivation, traditional black Corinthian grape sun-dried. Distinctive small dark seedless raisin (the original "currant" — etymologically derived from Corinth). Dark mahogany color, soft chewy texture, intensely sweet honey-grape-fig flavor — the Greek raisin-of-record, major export.', 'Greek pastry (revani, baklava variants); in sweet-and-savoury preparations (with chicken and rice); in fruit cakes; in muesli.', '["vacuum-pack-200g", "vacuum-pack-500g", "vacuum-pack-1kg", "professional-bulk-5kg", "gift-pack-300g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Korinthiaki", "Black Corinth raisin", "Currants", "Vostizza currants"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
