  ('9bdcf721-ce5b-2f29-2c56-2f457d5e6c79', 'GR', 'Greece', 'fruits_nuts', 'Fava Santorinis POP', '["Fava Santorinis POP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Aegean Santorini split-pea-puree-style yellow split-pea POP — distinctive — actually a yellow split pea (Lathyrus clymenum), not a fava bean. Cultivated in Santorini volcanic soil. Pale yellow color when dried, creamy mush when cooked, mild earthy-sweet flavor.', '**Iconic Cycladic Greek mezze** — Fava Santorinis (puree with capers, raw onion, EVOO, lemon); on mezze boards; pairs with Assyrtiko de Santorin.', '["vacuum-pack-dried-500g", "vacuum-pack-dried-1kg", "jar-cooked-puree-300g", "gift-pack-500g"]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, '["Fava Santorinis", "Santorini fava", "Yellow split pea"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
  ('f4a5ab29-67cc-4eb0-b937-e31946f563cf', 'GR', 'Greece', 'fruits_nuts', 'Tomataki Santorinis POP', '["Tomataki Santorinis POP"]'::jsonb, 'PDO', '["PDO"]'::jsonb, 'Aegean Santorini cherry tomato POP — distinctive — small intensely-flavored cherry tomato cultivated in Santorini volcanic soil with no irrigation, drawing only from sea-mist humidity. Bright deep-red small fruit, intensely sweet-tart concentrated flavor with characteristic volcanic-soil minerality.', 'Premium Cycladic centerpiece — in tomato salads, tomato fritters (tomatokeftedes — Santorinian classic), pasta sauces, fresh in mezze.', '["crate-fresh-2.5kg", "retail-tray-500g", "jar-tomato-paste-200g", "sun-dried-vacuum-pack-200g"]'::jsonb, '[6, 7, 8, 9]'::jsonb, '["Tomataki Santorinis", "Santorini tomato"]'::jsonb, FALSE, 'L2'),
